1
00:00:03,753 --> 00:00:08,542
'What happened to this city?
Pollution and smoke on either sides.'

2
00:00:08,804 --> 00:00:13,978
'Why does not anybody speak up?
Why should we tolerate it silently?'

3
00:00:14,058 --> 00:00:17,246
'Put an end to this
negligent attitude.'

4
00:00:17,492 --> 00:00:21,073
'Do not ignore any cigarette
or beedi that is lit.'

5
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:24,163
'Smoking is prohibited
at public places.'

6
00:00:24,446 --> 00:00:26,814
''Violation incurs fine.'

7
00:00:26,981 --> 00:00:29,580
'Do not smoke and let others smoke.'

8
00:00:29,977 --> 00:00:32,798
'Pay heavily if you smoke.'

9
00:00:33,481 --> 00:00:35,798
'Smoking causes cancer.'

10
00:00:36,479 --> 00:00:38,459
'Smoking kills.'

11
00:00:39,337 --> 00:00:42,974
Smoking causes cancer.
Smoking kills.

12
00:00:44,289 --> 00:00:47,237
'Drinking alcohol
is injurious to health.'

13
00:00:48,052 --> 00:00:50,928
'Drinking alcohol
is injurious to health.'

14
00:01:42,989 --> 00:01:46,187
I joined police services in
this area station five years back.

15
00:01:46,459 --> 00:01:48,884
Many sub-inspectors have
come and gone in this period.

16
00:01:49,141 --> 00:01:50,931
But you are the first S.I...

17
00:01:51,168 --> 00:01:54,923
Who has voluntarily enquired about
this case. That too on your first day.

18
00:01:55,004 --> 00:01:57,978
It is a good work, sir.
But I am telling out of concern.

19
00:01:58,058 --> 00:02:00,275
It is better not to interfere
in this case.

20
00:02:01,075 --> 00:02:04,527
This is a dangerous area.
And the case you are talking about..

21
00:02:04,701 --> 00:02:08,067
..it is not even registered.
That murder is just a rumour, sir.

22
00:02:08,146 --> 00:02:10,783
Just came to my ear, through
the grapevine. This is true, sir.

23
00:02:11,159 --> 00:02:14,175
It is okay. I like rumours
better than the truth.

24
00:02:14,705 --> 00:02:16,195
Tell me.

25
00:02:17,331 --> 00:02:19,769
They say it happened
eight years back.

26
00:02:19,848 --> 00:02:22,186
A lot of pigeon racing
happens in this area.

27
00:02:22,266 --> 00:02:24,182
There is talk that this murder..

28
00:02:24,263 --> 00:02:26,082
..was a result of
one of those fights.

29
00:02:26,459 --> 00:02:28,228
Pigeon racing? What is that?

30
00:02:28,307 --> 00:02:31,814
Sir, you never heard about it?
It is very common in Vizag, sir.

31
00:02:31,895 --> 00:02:33,376
But no one seems to know about it.

32
00:02:33,455 --> 00:02:35,848
There are two types
of pigeon racing, sir.

33
00:02:35,929 --> 00:02:37,556
One. Homing pigeon.

34
00:02:38,079 --> 00:02:39,745
Each participant enters..

35
00:02:39,824 --> 00:02:41,722
..about five to ten pigeons, sir.

36
00:02:41,802 --> 00:02:44,788
The day before the race, participants
bring their pigeons to the club.

37
00:02:45,073 --> 00:02:47,359
Each of the pigeons are given tags.

38
00:02:47,657 --> 00:02:51,113
A secret numbered ring
is fixed to the pigeon's leg.

39
00:02:54,497 --> 00:02:57,861
Then all pigeons are transported
through a lorry or train.

40
00:03:00,502 --> 00:03:04,414
Depending on the race distance,
they select a town.

41
00:03:04,725 --> 00:03:07,415
Like Nellore, Bhopal, Delhi.

42
00:03:08,468 --> 00:03:11,504
All the cages are lined up there.

43
00:03:11,585 --> 00:03:13,254
And all the pigeons
are released at once!

44
00:03:19,222 --> 00:03:21,623
No matter how far
away you take it..

45
00:03:21,774 --> 00:03:24,305
It flies right back
to its owner's place!

46
00:03:24,510 --> 00:03:26,743
The pigeon that reaches
first wins the race.

47
00:03:34,695 --> 00:03:37,354
Pigeon fanciers have
a lot of respect for it.

48
00:03:37,435 --> 00:03:39,149
They are running these
competitions since long time.

49
00:03:39,229 --> 00:03:40,938
They do not allow gambling
in these tournaments.

50
00:03:41,239 --> 00:03:43,268
But there is a lot
of competition and rivalry.

51
00:03:43,348 --> 00:03:45,100
There is talk that the murder
you are asking about..

52
00:03:45,180 --> 00:03:47,079
..happened during one such issue.

53
00:03:47,274 --> 00:03:47,986
Who did it?

54
00:03:48,067 --> 00:03:50,040
There is a notorious smuggler
called Velu in this area.

55
00:03:50,121 --> 00:03:50,841
You might have heard.

56
00:03:51,072 --> 00:03:53,688
He is very famous. This entire
area is under his control, sir.

57
00:03:53,769 --> 00:03:55,777
He exports red sanders
illegally, sir.

58
00:03:55,912 --> 00:03:58,532
Even he is been a pigeon
fancier for years.

59
00:03:58,659 --> 00:04:00,721
The killer was from his gang.

60
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:02,637
A twenty two year old boy!

61
00:04:03,168 --> 00:04:04,728
He was not even
a gangster back then.

62
00:04:04,807 --> 00:04:06,626
Just a boy who raised pigeons.

63
00:04:06,706 --> 00:04:09,424
He used to look after
Velu's racing pigeons.

64
00:04:09,503 --> 00:04:11,435
One night,
a guy from the opponent gang..

65
00:04:11,515 --> 00:04:14,078
..came in the night and slit
his favourite pigeon's throat.

66
00:04:14,943 --> 00:04:18,487
This boy went and stabbed
him to death in blind rage..

67
00:04:18,567 --> 00:04:20,555
..who was feared until then.

68
00:04:21,196 --> 00:04:23,247
Die! You!

69
00:04:24,579 --> 00:04:27,059
Hey! Who are you? Stop!

70
00:04:27,139 --> 00:04:31,655
He was just a boy who
raised pigeons until then.

71
00:04:31,735 --> 00:04:33,294
That was eight years back.

72
00:04:33,555 --> 00:04:35,283
He is the big-gun
in the hood these days.

73
00:04:35,511 --> 00:04:37,076
We can not even lay
a finger on him, sir.

74
00:04:37,658 --> 00:04:38,848
What did you say his name was?

75
00:04:40,108 --> 00:04:41,170
Maari.

76
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:01,298
Velu Anna has many
areas under his control.

77
00:05:01,379 --> 00:05:03,431
He handed one of
those areas to Maari.

78
00:05:07,262 --> 00:05:09,936
His cut reaches him
promptly every month.

79
00:05:11,197 --> 00:05:13,884
Velu Anna's main business
is smuggling red sanders.

80
00:05:14,119 --> 00:05:17,190
It is the top illegal business
in Chennai and Andhra these days.

81
00:05:17,329 --> 00:05:19,915
A tone of red sanders..

82
00:05:19,995 --> 00:05:21,392
..can fetch upto a million
at the foreign market.

83
00:05:21,473 --> 00:05:23,179
Velu Anna has too many
cases filed against him.

84
00:05:23,259 --> 00:05:25,078
And even more enemies.

85
00:05:25,158 --> 00:05:27,062
So he does not get out much.

86
00:05:27,362 --> 00:05:29,271
He handles all deals through Maari.

87
00:05:29,577 --> 00:05:32,049
There is another man
under Velu called Bird Ravi.

88
00:05:32,482 --> 00:05:34,969
He wants to be a
part of Velu's business.

89
00:05:35,048 --> 00:05:36,828
But Velu's support is for Maari.

90
00:05:37,002 --> 00:05:40,048
Velu does not interfere
in matters of Maari's area.

91
00:05:40,129 --> 00:05:42,223
Nothing happens here
without his consent.

92
00:05:43,065 --> 00:05:46,117
Want to pay up nicely?
Or should I smash your shop up?

93
00:05:46,197 --> 00:05:50,507
They are robbing us under broad daylight!
Is there no one to fight them?

94
00:06:03,764 --> 00:06:07,692
By standing in the
sun since long time..

95
00:06:07,771 --> 00:06:09,606
..they are requesting you.

96
00:06:09,766 --> 00:06:13,192
I will thrash you.. - Brother!
Brother! - You are all rowdies?

97
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:14,689
Why do you request him?

98
00:06:14,769 --> 00:06:18,444
Can not beat him up and get it?
- He is a ruffian. When he gets angry..

99
00:06:18,524 --> 00:06:20,262
..everyone around him flees.

100
00:06:20,343 --> 00:06:23,055
But when he is with his pigeon's..

101
00:06:23,437 --> 00:06:26,836
You can see his other side.
He immediately becomes kind!

102
00:06:27,031 --> 00:06:31,142
This bad guy appears to
be a good guy when he see pigeons.

103
00:06:32,778 --> 00:06:35,341
For ages,
Velu was hosting these tournaments.

104
00:06:35,487 --> 00:06:37,230
Then he left Maari in charge.

105
00:06:37,310 --> 00:06:41,391
Despite a lot of illegal businesses, he is
very honest when it comes to pigeons.

106
00:06:41,471 --> 00:06:43,563
He conducts these tournaments
supervised by senior fanciers.

107
00:06:43,644 --> 00:06:45,947
If someone cheats,
he gets very angry.

108
00:06:46,026 --> 00:06:48,377
He stops being kind.
Hard to deal with him then!

109
00:07:04,185 --> 00:07:06,274
He does not even spare
the people who are with them.

110
00:07:06,463 --> 00:07:09,576
There is a guy called Robert in his
gang. His pet name is 'Sannasi.'

111
00:07:09,656 --> 00:07:13,205
Whenever Maari gets angry,
he calls Sannasi from wherever he is..

112
00:07:13,286 --> 00:07:16,158
..he will beat him badly
and only then his anger is lost.

113
00:07:16,237 --> 00:07:19,557
Beer rates are hiked!
Why did they do it?

114
00:07:19,637 --> 00:07:21,882
There is another loafer
roaming with Maari.

115
00:07:21,963 --> 00:07:23,262
His name is Shanivaram.

116
00:07:23,504 --> 00:07:25,613
Shanivaram? What is this name?

117
00:07:25,815 --> 00:07:27,320
Saturday means..

118
00:07:27,488 --> 00:07:28,783
..drinking day.

119
00:07:28,863 --> 00:07:30,496
So you do not drink on other days?

120
00:07:30,576 --> 00:07:33,346
I will drink. - So you do not
drink on other days for sure?

121
00:07:33,427 --> 00:07:35,206
Oh dirty fellow!

122
00:07:35,286 --> 00:07:36,968
I drink on other days for sure.

123
00:07:37,048 --> 00:07:39,002
So why did you get
the name Shanivaram?

124
00:07:39,083 --> 00:07:41,518
I drink on saturdays at any cost.

125
00:07:42,771 --> 00:07:44,569
He is scratching his head.
I think he got confused.

126
00:07:45,197 --> 00:07:47,620
It happens this way
but we cannot do anything.

127
00:07:47,759 --> 00:07:49,445
He frightened everyone
to such extent.

128
00:07:49,593 --> 00:07:51,453
There was a tournament
in that area yesterday too.

129
00:07:51,661 --> 00:07:53,235
As usual Maari won the cup.

130
00:07:53,315 --> 00:07:55,262
Sir, we cannot tolerate
the antics they do today.

131
00:08:35,698 --> 00:08:40,401
"His name- Prominent!
This guy.- He is different!"

132
00:08:40,481 --> 00:08:45,519
"He paves new routes.
With his steel heart he rules."

133
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:50,793
"His soul knows no guilt."

134
00:08:50,874 --> 00:08:55,697
"He is seen all maladies.
And misery."

135
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:58,420
"Maari!"

136
00:08:58,658 --> 00:09:03,269
"He is the good one. - He is Maari!
The dashing one. - Maari!"

137
00:09:03,655 --> 00:09:08,739
"Rub him and he is gold,. Snub
him and he is a beast, this Maari!"

138
00:09:08,820 --> 00:09:13,739
"He is the good one. - He is Maari!
The dashing one. - Maari!"

139
00:09:13,818 --> 00:09:17,534
"Rub him and he is gold,
Snub him and he is a beast, this Maari!"

140
00:10:06,701 --> 00:10:11,576
"Does not know the world.
Does not heed law and order."

141
00:10:11,768 --> 00:10:16,677
"Does not like to change his ways."

142
00:10:16,756 --> 00:10:21,592
"Does not have time for love.
Do not try threatening him."

143
00:10:21,673 --> 00:10:29,519
"He is a solo contestant.
Do not you dare pick on him."

144
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:34,243
"Rub him and he is gold.
Snub him and he is a beast, this Maari!"

145
00:10:34,643 --> 00:10:37,463
"Rub him and he is gold.
Snub him and he is a beast, this Maari!"

146
00:10:43,494 --> 00:10:47,545
Today is Boss' birthday. We have
to laugh a lot. We are hired for work.

147
00:10:47,625 --> 00:10:50,703
You both will get thrashed.
- I have got a special item here for Boss!

148
00:10:50,783 --> 00:10:52,114
Ugh!

149
00:10:52,365 --> 00:10:53,864
Feels light weight.

150
00:10:53,998 --> 00:10:56,974
What is that?
- Your favourite item.

151
00:10:57,379 --> 00:10:58,673
Hey, come out.

152
00:11:04,366 --> 00:11:06,401
Who is he?
- Product name: Anirudh.

153
00:11:06,481 --> 00:11:08,770
Ani.. - Rudh! Rudh!
- Rudh?

154
00:11:09,027 --> 00:11:10,905
What does he do?
- He plays! - What?

155
00:11:10,985 --> 00:11:13,647
He plays music and sings well.

156
00:11:14,115 --> 00:11:16,265
Perform for us.
- I need some instruments, man.

157
00:11:16,346 --> 00:11:17,960
Get him those instruments.

158
00:11:19,836 --> 00:11:23,791
Why? Cool. Cool! - Not necessary.
Just sing and dance.

159
00:11:23,929 --> 00:11:26,158
Okay, I will do it.
- Careful.

160
00:11:26,342 --> 00:11:31,927
Ugh! What is his dress? Look at his
cap and glasses! Get him changed.

161
00:11:32,294 --> 00:11:34,045
Come, dear.
- Hey! Hey! Bro..

162
00:11:34,125 --> 00:11:35,360
Come.

163
00:12:07,037 --> 00:12:08,569
Sir, it is better for us..

164
00:12:08,649 --> 00:12:10,635
..to remain silent by letting his
do his work. - Greetings, sir.

165
00:12:11,443 --> 00:12:13,901
Sir, where are we going?
- Take the vehicle to Maari's area.

166
00:12:15,847 --> 00:12:17,202
We have got information that..

167
00:12:17,283 --> 00:12:19,250
..betting is taking place
at the pigeon tournament today.

168
00:12:19,807 --> 00:12:22,014
We will go there and
catch him red handed.

169
00:12:22,095 --> 00:12:24,362
But without asking them..

170
00:12:24,442 --> 00:12:25,788
We should not enter their area.

171
00:12:25,868 --> 00:12:28,062
Are we the police or is he?

172
00:12:28,142 --> 00:12:29,433
Start the jeep.

173
00:12:43,971 --> 00:12:46,355
Hey, you are banned
this year, right?

174
00:12:46,436 --> 00:12:48,301
What are you doing here?
Just leave.

175
00:12:48,474 --> 00:12:51,762
I just came to watch.
Can not I watch? - Just leave.

176
00:12:54,152 --> 00:12:55,812
Sir, he tumbled once!

177
00:12:55,893 --> 00:12:58,197
Bro, was that okay?
- That was okay.

178
00:12:59,157 --> 00:13:01,382
Why is it descending already?

179
00:13:01,461 --> 00:13:03,274
Looks like he will not make it!

180
00:13:10,292 --> 00:13:12,086
Who is that aunt?

181
00:13:12,421 --> 00:13:14,890
You are pretending to flail your
cloth and making the bird fly away!

182
00:13:14,970 --> 00:13:17,297
I do not even know that woman.
Must be a neighbour.

183
00:13:17,376 --> 00:13:19,995
Do not you see that tournament
is held here? Go inside.

184
00:13:20,075 --> 00:13:23,233
He is lying.
- Yes. - She is his wife.

185
00:13:23,312 --> 00:13:25,951
You have set her up? - No, brother.
- Why would you set-up your own wife?

186
00:13:26,032 --> 00:13:28,227
Is she your wife or a set-up?
- Did we come for her?

187
00:13:28,307 --> 00:13:30,923
Note that down! That his
bird has lost. - No, brother.

188
00:13:31,003 --> 00:13:32,892
Do not play your tricks
in Maari's tournament.

189
00:13:32,971 --> 00:13:33,981
You!

190
00:13:36,645 --> 00:13:38,918
How come I hear a jeep in here?

191
00:13:52,793 --> 00:13:54,563
Where is Maari?
- Look at that!

192
00:13:54,769 --> 00:13:57,177
Firstly, you should not have
walked in without our permission.

193
00:13:57,378 --> 00:13:59,985
And you have the
guts to ask for Maari?

194
00:14:00,065 --> 00:14:02,052
I have got information
that betting happens here.

195
00:14:02,131 --> 00:14:05,311
Betting? - The jeep must
be heading towards Poorna market.

196
00:14:05,392 --> 00:14:06,707
Must have lost its
way and ended up here.

197
00:14:06,787 --> 00:14:09,052
We are just letting the pigeons
fly and looking at the skies..

198
00:14:09,133 --> 00:14:11,181
..but you are using
big words like betting.

199
00:14:11,260 --> 00:14:14,507
You can not organise such tournaments
without police permission.

200
00:14:14,647 --> 00:14:16,403
Stop everything.
I need to see Maari.

201
00:14:16,484 --> 00:14:18,884
Clear the crowd!
- What is the noise?

202
00:14:34,102 --> 00:14:36,276
Did you ask for protection?
- No, Maari.

203
00:14:39,744 --> 00:14:41,192
Then what is the officer doing here?

204
00:14:42,792 --> 00:14:45,143
A cop's job is where
the rowdies are.

205
00:14:45,371 --> 00:14:46,670
Rowdies?

206
00:14:47,066 --> 00:14:50,783
We are flying the symbol
of peace and you call us rowdies?

207
00:14:51,044 --> 00:14:54,087
Big shots participate in this,
there is nothing wrong.

208
00:14:54,634 --> 00:14:56,951
Some enemy of mine
has told you lies about me.

209
00:14:57,961 --> 00:14:59,912
Only a man who does
wrong will have enemies.

210
00:15:06,634 --> 00:15:07,877
You should leave, sir.

211
00:15:08,539 --> 00:15:10,918
Will not be nice if we force you out.

212
00:15:13,644 --> 00:15:15,844
Your threats will not scare me.

213
00:15:16,379 --> 00:15:17,399
I have got evidence.

214
00:15:17,850 --> 00:15:21,805
Just stop everything and co-operate
to the investigation. - Evidence?

215
00:15:23,567 --> 00:15:26,888
Evidence.. Evidence..

216
00:15:29,846 --> 00:15:32,934
Hey! Come here, boy.

217
00:15:33,219 --> 00:15:36,138
He will not hit you!
- Come.

218
00:15:36,677 --> 00:15:38,072
Come!

219
00:15:39,168 --> 00:15:43,144
You got into a mess
when you cheated last year.

220
00:15:43,299 --> 00:15:46,302
I banned you this year because
you can not pay up the entry fees.

221
00:15:46,465 --> 00:15:49,787
But you should not go to the
officer and tell him lies about me!

222
00:15:50,972 --> 00:15:51,892
Tell me.

223
00:15:51,972 --> 00:15:54,924
Does anything illegal happen?
- Hello! Leave him.

224
00:15:55,004 --> 00:15:57,125
Talk to me.
- One minute. I am asking.

225
00:15:57,206 --> 00:16:00,663
Tell me.
Anything illegal happening? Ask.

226
00:16:00,744 --> 00:16:05,379
Leave him! - Tell! - Anything
illegal happening. I am asking.

227
00:16:05,460 --> 00:16:07,018
Hey!
- Hey!

228
00:16:15,133 --> 00:16:17,422
Let is leave, sir.

229
00:16:19,578 --> 00:16:21,943
Did not he say nothing
illegal happens here?

230
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:25,600
Leave!

231
00:16:25,679 --> 00:16:27,453
Come, sir!

232
00:16:34,003 --> 00:16:37,068
Who is he? - The new sub-inspector
in the area, Maari.

233
00:16:44,735 --> 00:16:47,533
If you do stupid things again..

234
00:16:49,178 --> 00:16:50,733
..I will rip you apart.

235
00:16:59,049 --> 00:17:01,870
Maari!

236
00:17:02,938 --> 00:17:05,072
Maari!

237
00:17:06,845 --> 00:17:09,223
Maari!

238
00:17:10,539 --> 00:17:12,851
Maari!

239
00:17:16,781 --> 00:17:19,999
Will not be nice if we forced you out.

240
00:17:19,080 --> 00:17:21,100
Hey!
- Hey!

241
00:17:22,571 --> 00:17:26,216
Sir, do not think
about it all the time.

242
00:17:26,472 --> 00:17:27,894
What can we do?

243
00:17:28,211 --> 00:17:29,788
Big shots are behind him.

244
00:17:30,071 --> 00:17:32,288
We have to ignore it.

245
00:17:32,813 --> 00:17:35,256
Not just you, all the policemen.

246
00:17:35,571 --> 00:17:37,817
I am not like all the policemen,
Hanumanth.

247
00:17:38,435 --> 00:17:40,709
He is known to have
committed a murder.

248
00:17:41,067 --> 00:17:43,211
What is the use of being policemen
when we can not lock him up?

249
00:17:43,384 --> 00:17:46,276
How can we act upon rumours?

250
00:17:46,576 --> 00:17:49,469
It is still a rumour because
everyone let it be that way.

251
00:17:49,653 --> 00:17:50,980
Someone told you this rumour.

252
00:17:51,059 --> 00:17:54,046
Someone else told him.
If we follow the trail..

253
00:17:54,470 --> 00:17:55,913
..it will not be hearsay.

254
00:17:56,326 --> 00:17:58,182
We will find the origin.

255
00:17:58,261 --> 00:17:59,663
We will start tomorrow.

256
00:17:59,921 --> 00:18:03,103
We will start with
you and connect till Maari.

257
00:18:04,017 --> 00:18:05,851
Mom!
- What?

258
00:18:05,931 --> 00:18:08,103
You said you will
buy me a new bag, mom!

259
00:18:08,182 --> 00:18:09,864
I am struggling to make ends meet.

260
00:18:09,943 --> 00:18:12,213
You want a new bag?

261
00:18:12,294 --> 00:18:15,145
Use the one you already have.
- It is torn, mom!

262
00:18:15,224 --> 00:18:17,223
Everyone in school makes fun.

263
00:18:17,304 --> 00:18:19,910
I will stitch it tomorrow.
Use it for now.

264
00:18:19,990 --> 00:18:21,355
Do not irritate me.

265
00:18:21,434 --> 00:18:23,359
I will not go to school..

266
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:26,420
..if you do not get me a new bag.
- Do not go, then.

267
00:18:26,586 --> 00:18:28,919
What do I care?
Bugging me in the mornings!

268
00:18:28,999 --> 00:18:32,909
Mom, please buy a new one. Please!
- Hey!

269
00:18:32,989 --> 00:18:37,328
Loudspeaker Kavitha! - I am pissed
off already. Do not interfere.

270
00:18:37,409 --> 00:18:41,107
Please, mom. - Your yelling woke
me up in the morning.

271
00:18:41,186 --> 00:18:42,599
And now you are pissed?

272
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:44,467
You do not even have a sweet voice.

273
00:18:44,628 --> 00:18:46,935
You are shouting like a sheep.

274
00:18:47,413 --> 00:18:50,607
Look, mom!
He is always making fun of me.

275
00:18:50,688 --> 00:18:53,786
You know he is pulling your leg.
Why are you still standing here?

276
00:18:53,865 --> 00:18:56,694
You are getting late, go to school.

277
00:18:56,968 --> 00:18:58,935
This has become a routine!

278
00:18:59,085 --> 00:19:00,996
Why are you teasing her?

279
00:19:01,076 --> 00:19:02,614
What were you doing, then?

280
00:19:03,202 --> 00:19:04,751
Are you not shouting?

281
00:19:05,135 --> 00:19:06,339
She asked for the bag, right?

282
00:19:06,420 --> 00:19:09,259
Why do not you buy it?
- Where do I get the money?

283
00:19:10,105 --> 00:19:12,300
If your husband does not drink for
two days, you will get the money.

284
00:19:12,381 --> 00:19:14,764
You talk so much,
why can not you buy her one?

285
00:19:14,844 --> 00:19:16,491
I would have bought
it if you had married me.

286
00:19:16,571 --> 00:19:18,642
You missed your chance.

287
00:19:18,826 --> 00:19:20,107
Look at that face!

288
00:19:23,828 --> 00:19:27,607
Maari, Did someone tell you they
are moving into house number 8?

289
00:19:28,760 --> 00:19:30,740
No. No one told me. Why?

290
00:19:30,990 --> 00:19:33,954
Then someone has moved
in without our permission.

291
00:19:49,628 --> 00:19:53,245
What are you doing here?
Stop! Stop!

292
00:19:53,681 --> 00:19:55,486
Painting without permission.

293
00:19:56,038 --> 00:19:59,454
Stop it, I say!
No respect for a gangster!

294
00:19:59,535 --> 00:20:00,776
Move aside.

295
00:20:00,855 --> 00:20:02,810
Oh, sorry. It is a mannequin.
- Why are you just standing there?

296
00:20:02,891 --> 00:20:04,829
Here, hang this.
- Okay, ma'am.

297
00:20:04,909 --> 00:20:06,067
What?

298
00:20:06,146 --> 00:20:09,102
She asked me to hang this against
the wall. - Why not her face?

299
00:20:09,287 --> 00:20:11,944
Taking orders from a woman!
We are gangsters?

300
00:20:12,596 --> 00:20:15,014
What is this?
- What?

301
00:20:15,521 --> 00:20:18,502
If you move in here and shift
your belongings without informing..

302
00:20:18,583 --> 00:20:21,423
Should we keep quiet?
- Who are you? Why should I tell you?

303
00:20:21,563 --> 00:20:24,094
Whatever happens in the area,
happens only with Maari's permission.

304
00:20:24,238 --> 00:20:25,949
Got it, white bro?
- What?

305
00:20:26,028 --> 00:20:28,574
Are you doing rowdyism?
- I was doing comedy till now.

306
00:20:28,730 --> 00:20:30,173
Now I am doing rowdyism.

307
00:20:30,253 --> 00:20:33,064
Here, this is rowdyism.
- Please! Please!

308
00:20:33,388 --> 00:20:35,511
That house broker never
told us anything about this.

309
00:20:35,592 --> 00:20:37,218
He said he told you.

310
00:20:37,298 --> 00:20:40,973
No, sir! When did you tell us?
- Not to you, sir. - Then?

311
00:20:43,700 --> 00:20:45,026
I told her, sir.

312
00:21:28,886 --> 00:21:31,585
Slap you!
- Hey Maari, control yourself!

313
00:21:31,664 --> 00:21:34,288
It is morning time.
- Think you can touch me?

314
00:21:34,633 --> 00:21:37,692
Had you not been a woman,
I would have ruined you. - No.

315
00:21:37,771 --> 00:21:39,431
Do not do anything to my daughter.

316
00:21:39,510 --> 00:21:41,870
Poor thing, she made a mistake.
- She keeps talking..

317
00:21:42,550 --> 00:21:43,806
..what did we do wrong?

318
00:21:43,885 --> 00:21:45,923
We only did our duty, right?
- Yes, yes.

319
00:21:46,003 --> 00:21:47,811
Did the broker tell
you anything? - Yes.

320
00:21:47,892 --> 00:21:49,884
Why did not you tell us anything?
- Mother..

321
00:21:49,964 --> 00:21:51,506
Why should we pay them up?

322
00:21:51,586 --> 00:21:54,354
It seems I need to pay
them extra to open a boutique.

323
00:21:54,433 --> 00:21:57,423
So mother and daughter are
planning to open a petty shop here?

324
00:21:58,087 --> 00:21:59,431
No. Not a petty shop.

325
00:21:59,510 --> 00:22:01,950
Boutique.
- Mother..

326
00:22:02,346 --> 00:22:04,395
Why are you explaining
all this to them?

327
00:22:04,476 --> 00:22:05,950
Look.
- Hey!

328
00:22:06,596 --> 00:22:09,567
Break your finger! Drop it.

329
00:22:10,195 --> 00:22:11,270
This is my house.

330
00:22:11,583 --> 00:22:13,812
I will do as I wish. Okay?

331
00:22:13,892 --> 00:22:15,155
Look girl..

332
00:22:15,236 --> 00:22:18,062
Keep your petty shop.

333
00:22:18,142 --> 00:22:20,479
Keep him if you want.
- Yes!

334
00:22:20,558 --> 00:22:22,268
But who will give you
protection for all that?

335
00:22:22,347 --> 00:22:25,348
Give us our cut,
and keep whatever you want.

336
00:22:25,429 --> 00:22:27,717
Protection? For what?

337
00:22:27,890 --> 00:22:29,847
What will happen here?
-Anything could happen.

338
00:22:30,836 --> 00:22:32,209
This glass could fall and shatter.

339
00:22:34,616 --> 00:22:37,409
That cupboard could topple
and break. -Do not do that, sir.

340
00:22:38,038 --> 00:22:40,570
Maari, something lighter, please!

341
00:22:41,010 --> 00:22:43,096
Okay. Someone might break the TV.

342
00:22:43,234 --> 00:22:45,107
Do not break the T.V.

343
00:22:45,263 --> 00:22:48,283
Just give them the money.
- Take.

344
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:50,692
This covers the house,
who will pay for the petty shop?

345
00:22:50,771 --> 00:22:52,057
Boutique!
- What do you say?

346
00:22:53,563 --> 00:22:55,362
You will have to pay double for
English names.

347
00:22:55,442 --> 00:22:58,623
I do not have cash in hand.
Give us some time. I will pay later.

348
00:22:59,463 --> 00:23:00,751
One week.

349
00:23:00,891 --> 00:23:02,428
I will file police complaint.

350
00:23:02,508 --> 00:23:04,740
We are going to the police
station for the next collection.

351
00:23:07,279 --> 00:23:08,840
No, Maari.

352
00:23:15,732 --> 00:23:18,147
Her eyes are too big.

353
00:23:18,308 --> 00:23:20,279
The way you were staring at her,
I was happy.

354
00:23:20,359 --> 00:23:22,221
I thought you were in love!
- What?

355
00:23:22,301 --> 00:23:25,125
Love? For the first time,
I felt like slapping a girl.

356
00:23:25,204 --> 00:23:27,548
I have a principle against
hitting women. So I let it go.

357
00:23:27,627 --> 00:23:29,982
Maari, we have seen
in so many Telugu movies.

358
00:23:30,063 --> 00:23:33,036
The heroine swears in slow motion.

359
00:23:33,115 --> 00:23:34,828
The hero takes it
with a smile on his face.

360
00:23:34,909 --> 00:23:36,372
And they fall in love.

361
00:23:36,506 --> 00:23:38,563
How can you fall in love when
a woman is yelling at your face?

362
00:23:38,643 --> 00:23:40,881
I would rather catch
chikungunya than fall in love.

363
00:23:40,961 --> 00:23:42,352
Then my route is clear.
- What?

364
00:23:42,432 --> 00:23:43,724
No, I meant this is the route to go.

365
00:23:43,805 --> 00:23:46,330
That girl talks too much,
keep her under control.

366
00:23:54,578 --> 00:23:55,943
Hi Gajuwaka!

367
00:23:57,107 --> 00:23:58,472
Felt shock?

368
00:23:58,762 --> 00:24:00,581
I will go in my route.

369
00:24:00,808 --> 00:24:04,363
Maari Boys are hosting
11th Annual Tumbler Pigeon and..

370
00:24:04,442 --> 00:24:07,461
..High Flyer Pigeon Competition.
We are having a prize distribution.

371
00:24:07,651 --> 00:24:09,218
When we call out your name,
come and collect your prizes.

372
00:24:09,646 --> 00:24:11,696
One important thing..

373
00:24:11,875 --> 00:24:16,786
Some people fly their pigeons every year
just for the consolation prizes.

374
00:24:16,931 --> 00:24:19,866
We have got some vessels for you.
You can collect them and go.

375
00:24:19,946 --> 00:24:21,883
Medals, bro.
- Whatever, give it to them.

376
00:24:22,195 --> 00:24:25,271
Maari is here. Applause!

377
00:24:26,208 --> 00:24:28,932
Maari and the oldies
will greet each other.

378
00:24:35,770 --> 00:24:38,267
The first prize goes
to Maari's pigeon as usual.

379
00:24:38,346 --> 00:24:40,684
As we are hosting it,
we will be magnanimous.

380
00:24:40,765 --> 00:24:43,343
But the counsellor still want..

381
00:24:43,423 --> 00:24:44,893
..to give prize to Maari.

382
00:24:45,171 --> 00:24:48,018
Clap! Louder! - After
all those foreign medicines..

383
00:24:48,097 --> 00:24:50,269
..all we get is
the consolation prize?

384
00:24:50,682 --> 00:24:53,072
This Maari does something special.

385
00:24:53,222 --> 00:24:55,557
Our birds have no
value in the market.

386
00:24:55,724 --> 00:24:57,721
Even people from
Delhi and Calcutta..

387
00:24:57,800 --> 00:24:59,916
..want Maari's birds.

388
00:25:00,301 --> 00:25:02,491
We will change everything tomorrow.

389
00:25:02,770 --> 00:25:04,280
Next prize.

390
00:25:04,499 --> 00:25:07,485
Consolation Prize.
Come on stage, Bird Ravi.

391
00:25:08,023 --> 00:25:11,440
You go get it. - Hey, you are Bird
Ravi, right? You should come up.

392
00:25:11,520 --> 00:25:12,955
I am coming.

393
00:25:13,692 --> 00:25:15,642
Put it on his head.

394
00:25:16,445 --> 00:25:17,849
Put it.

395
00:25:18,909 --> 00:25:20,291
Enough, enough.

396
00:25:21,176 --> 00:25:22,324
Enough.

397
00:25:23,695 --> 00:25:27,301
Bird Ravi wishes to organise a
Tumbler-High Flyer tournament tomorrow.

398
00:25:28,487 --> 00:25:30,276
Nothing happens
outside your control.

399
00:25:30,355 --> 00:25:32,983
It only works if
one person does it.

400
00:25:33,064 --> 00:25:34,661
If there is some problem..

401
00:25:34,740 --> 00:25:36,391
Maari's name is at stake
for granting permission.

402
00:25:36,471 --> 00:25:38,528
You are the host, you are the winner.

403
00:25:38,673 --> 00:25:41,587
Why will there be any fight?
- What are you trying to say?

404
00:25:41,821 --> 00:25:43,816
That we win because we host?

405
00:25:43,896 --> 00:25:46,769
I am not saying.
Anyways, you will win.

406
00:25:46,849 --> 00:25:49,984
At least we will have
the pride of hosting it.

407
00:25:50,065 --> 00:25:52,125
It will boost our
pigeon's market value.

408
00:25:52,205 --> 00:25:54,814
Earlier, a Bird Ravi's
pigeon had some value.

409
00:25:54,894 --> 00:25:56,991
Now everyone comes
after only your pigeons.

410
00:25:57,071 --> 00:25:58,790
We are asking this as a favour.

411
00:25:58,871 --> 00:26:01,283
We have got the money
and the manpower to host it.

412
00:26:01,363 --> 00:26:04,730
We will give you your
share of the entry fees.

413
00:26:04,810 --> 00:26:07,400
You can participate,
you do not have to pay an entry fee.

414
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:11,028
Wow! What an offer.
- Very generous.

415
00:26:11,339 --> 00:26:13,878
I said it like it is.

416
00:26:18,035 --> 00:26:20,598
Hosting or paying
is not the matter here.

417
00:26:20,815 --> 00:26:23,048
You should maintain the sanctity of
the tournament. That is important.

418
00:26:23,128 --> 00:26:26,742
We will handle all that, Maari.
You should give us a chance once.

419
00:26:26,961 --> 00:26:29,088
Okay. Let is give it a shot.

420
00:26:34,211 --> 00:26:36,034
Thanks, Maari.
- But we are not flying our birds.

421
00:26:36,114 --> 00:26:39,675
Why, Maari?
- You said we always win it.

422
00:26:39,824 --> 00:26:41,807
Why piss you off? - No, Maari.

423
00:26:41,886 --> 00:26:44,509
We will be very proud if
your pigeon wins in our tournament.

424
00:26:56,907 --> 00:26:59,923
When did I tell you about
the murder? Stop babbling.

425
00:27:00,085 --> 00:27:01,723
You told me right here,
the other night.

426
00:27:01,804 --> 00:27:04,833
Are you out of your mind?
- You are enquiring about him here?

427
00:27:04,913 --> 00:27:07,056
Sir, I just blurted
some nonsense, sir.

428
00:27:07,194 --> 00:27:09,191
Tea shop owner Satyam told me.

429
00:27:09,971 --> 00:27:11,451
Officer, I do not know anything.

430
00:27:11,531 --> 00:27:13,636
I might have believed you
if you had not spilt the tea.

431
00:27:13,717 --> 00:27:14,947
Tell me the truth.

432
00:27:15,027 --> 00:27:16,694
Some say it happened..

433
00:27:16,775 --> 00:27:19,303
..some say it did not happen.
- Who are these people?

434
00:27:19,383 --> 00:27:21,961
This guy called Murthy,
in the 2nd street. - Murthy?

435
00:27:22,195 --> 00:27:23,906
That drunkard?

436
00:27:23,987 --> 00:27:28,008
The murder happened for real
during a gang war eight years back.

437
00:27:28,087 --> 00:27:31,067
That is all I know. - Everything
we heard since morning is a waste.

438
00:27:31,201 --> 00:27:32,355
There is one person called Apparao.

439
00:27:32,539 --> 00:27:34,211
Father and son pick pockets.

440
00:27:34,291 --> 00:27:36,272
Dad is old school, does a neat job.

441
00:27:36,602 --> 00:27:37,706
But the son is a rookie.

442
00:27:38,357 --> 00:27:40,842
He was caught while stealing
chain in the market last week.

443
00:27:41,094 --> 00:27:43,924
The guy got away,
but everyone saw his face.

444
00:27:44,005 --> 00:27:46,209
His case is registered,
we can use that to threaten him.

445
00:27:46,782 --> 00:27:49,612
Eight years back,
Maari committed a murder.

446
00:27:49,980 --> 00:27:51,491
What do you know about it?

447
00:27:51,659 --> 00:27:53,816
About murder?

448
00:27:54,328 --> 00:27:57,143
I do not know anything.

449
00:27:57,294 --> 00:27:59,239
Someone has given
you false information.

450
00:27:59,428 --> 00:28:02,130
So, shall we lock your son up?

451
00:28:02,210 --> 00:28:03,959
Sir. - Yeah, there is
a case registered against him.

452
00:28:04,332 --> 00:28:07,397
Answer them, dad.
- What do you want to know about Maari?

453
00:28:07,477 --> 00:28:09,759
Keep quiet!
- Why are you scared?

454
00:28:09,965 --> 00:28:10,924
What can he do to us?

455
00:28:11,404 --> 00:28:13,734
Ask me, sir.
- Answer bravely.

456
00:28:13,815 --> 00:28:16,048
No one will know about this.
Speak up!

457
00:28:18,192 --> 00:28:21,498
Back then,
Velu's gang was not in power.

458
00:28:21,625 --> 00:28:25,058
There was a man called Pandu.
He was the top gun.

459
00:28:25,443 --> 00:28:28,235
Those two gangs
never got along, sir.

460
00:28:28,403 --> 00:28:31,448
One day, because of some issue..

461
00:28:31,876 --> 00:28:34,239
They say Maari went
and stabbed Pandu.

462
00:28:34,930 --> 00:28:37,298
Then it turned into a gang war..

463
00:28:37,453 --> 00:28:39,626
..and Pandu's entire
gang was wiped out.

464
00:28:39,844 --> 00:28:41,605
Since then..

465
00:28:41,684 --> 00:28:43,821
..Velu Anna's hold over
the area became stronger.

466
00:28:44,250 --> 00:28:46,713
Do you know anyone
who witnessed the killing?

467
00:28:46,892 --> 00:28:48,006
No sir.

468
00:28:48,086 --> 00:28:51,153
I have not heard of anyone who
witnessed Maari committing the murder.

469
00:28:51,521 --> 00:28:53,410
The case was not registered.

470
00:28:53,490 --> 00:28:55,282
Then when Velu came to power..

471
00:28:55,363 --> 00:28:57,538
..he wiped it clean.
- How is that?

472
00:28:58,208 --> 00:29:00,248
They have killed
a man who was in power.

473
00:29:00,414 --> 00:29:02,521
Maari became a gangster
only after that.

474
00:29:02,866 --> 00:29:05,018
The whole area is scared of him.

475
00:29:05,625 --> 00:29:08,461
But no one knows who
finished him, or how.

476
00:29:08,723 --> 00:29:09,954
How would we know?

477
00:29:10,246 --> 00:29:12,331
If something like that
happens then only we will know.

478
00:29:12,411 --> 00:29:14,225
You only tell the truth.

479
00:29:14,305 --> 00:29:15,345
For any rowdy..

480
00:29:15,424 --> 00:29:16,859
..a murder like this..

481
00:29:17,044 --> 00:29:18,509
..is a matter of pride.

482
00:29:18,671 --> 00:29:21,105
Then why is it still a rumour?

483
00:29:21,444 --> 00:29:23,547
Because it never happened, sir.

484
00:29:23,626 --> 00:29:26,296
It is just building up, sir.
Do not believe any of it.

485
00:29:28,865 --> 00:29:30,893
What is this? Hi dear.

486
00:29:30,972 --> 00:29:32,136
