00:58:03,536 --> 00:58:05,862
Then I go to meet Velu Anna.
If he gives me some work, I do it.

976
00:58:05,943 --> 00:58:06,981
Then the boys come over..

977
00:58:07,061 --> 00:58:09,713
..I have fun, get drunk and sleep.
That is all I do.

978
00:58:09,793 --> 00:58:12,795
Not that..
How do I explain..

979
00:58:13,557 --> 00:58:17,128
Even if you are a good person,
you are a rowdy.

980
00:58:17,208 --> 00:58:21,949
Oh.. - I would be scared, right?
How will my parents ever accept?

981
00:58:22,505 --> 00:58:23,903
We will finish them off?

982
00:58:23,983 --> 00:58:25,460
What?

983
00:58:25,965 --> 00:58:30,251
No! I do not know you well enough.
How can I trust you?

984
00:58:30,331 --> 00:58:35,014
You do not need to trust me. Let this go.
Do not let it confuse you. Bye!

985
00:58:38,672 --> 00:58:45,360
"The Prince who rules the world.
That is me."

986
00:58:45,864 --> 00:58:52,864
"You are the Princess
who stole my heart."

987
00:58:52,945 --> 00:58:54,849
Maari!

988
00:58:55,268 --> 00:58:57,006
Something wrong.

989
00:58:57,197 --> 00:58:59,567
What happened?
- Not there, Maari.

990
00:58:59,648 --> 00:59:02,528
Why does not that girl like you?
- Do not know.

991
00:59:02,608 --> 00:59:05,432
Did you tell her properly?

992
00:59:05,797 --> 00:59:10,803
I told her I love you in every possible
way! - Do not say like that, Maari.

993
00:59:11,414 --> 00:59:16,349
I.. - I.. - Love..
- Love.. - You.. - You..

994
00:59:16,664 --> 00:59:20,621
Say like this. - Why do
you split it in three like that?

995
00:59:20,701 --> 00:59:23,481
Because it is three words!

996
00:59:23,561 --> 00:59:27,180
What? Is not'I love you'
a single word.

997
00:59:27,260 --> 00:59:32,749
No. - No? - No. - So why did not
you tell me this before?

998
00:59:32,829 --> 00:59:34,692
Shanivaram!

999
00:59:34,840 --> 00:59:38,846
Your girl? - Why have
you brought this girl here?

1000
00:59:38,927 --> 00:59:41,378
She wanted to talk to you,
brother.

1001
00:59:43,708 --> 00:59:47,280
You have come to develop
our friendship? Come.

1002
00:59:47,532 --> 00:59:52,288
Sit. Sit. - Go. You too go.
Come in the morning. You sit.

1003
00:59:52,597 --> 00:59:56,287
Want a drink?
- No. - She must be drunk already.

1004
00:59:56,367 --> 01:00:01,144
You only drink in star hotels.
- I need to talk to you. - Talk.

1005
01:00:02,199 --> 01:00:05,356
I did not tell you
that I do not like you.

1006
01:00:05,666 --> 01:00:07,863
I just wanted to
know more about you.

1007
01:00:08,068 --> 01:00:12,766
But you had left by then. - What
do you want to know? - Who are you?

1008
01:00:13,266 --> 01:00:14,876
How did you turn out this way?

1009
01:00:17,480 --> 01:00:19,186
Turn out what way?

1010
01:00:19,860 --> 01:00:24,358
Turn out what way?
- No, everyone fears you.

1011
01:00:24,699 --> 01:00:26,452
Including me.

1012
01:00:27,260 --> 01:00:29,530
Do I look like a rapist?

1013
01:00:31,081 --> 01:00:32,893
Only gutless men rape.

1014
01:00:33,503 --> 01:00:35,083
I am a real man.

1015
01:00:35,280 --> 01:00:38,057
Real men do not rape.
- No, no..

1016
01:00:38,581 --> 01:00:40,167
I know about you.

1017
01:00:40,367 --> 01:00:41,978
But everyone is so scared of you.

1018
01:00:42,342 --> 01:00:45,540
There must be some reason.
Violence.

1019
01:00:46,675 --> 01:00:48,000
Murders..

1020
01:00:50,023 --> 01:00:51,253
Murder?

1021
01:00:55,456 --> 01:00:56,806
Nothing of that sort.

1022
01:01:07,518 --> 01:01:09,221
Murder..

1023
01:01:10,251 --> 01:01:11,942
Can not really call it a murder.

1024
01:01:14,965 --> 01:01:16,981
Murder..

1025
01:01:17,836 --> 01:01:21,434
Something like murder.
Pretty much murder.

1026
01:01:22,978 --> 01:01:24,905
There was this guy
called Pandu in my town.

1027
01:01:25,786 --> 01:01:28,643
Real big shot. Not any one
could have laid a finger on him.

1028
01:01:28,889 --> 01:01:30,911
One day I just went
and casually stabbed him.

1029
01:01:32,789 --> 01:01:35,038
Who are you? Anna!

1030
01:01:35,474 --> 01:01:38,275
But he did not die.
So it does not count as murder.

1031
01:01:38,356 --> 01:01:43,940
Someone else finished him off
two days later. But I got all the credit.

1032
01:01:49,739 --> 01:01:52,413
It will not work out.
Go home and think all night.

1033
01:01:52,492 --> 01:01:54,717
If it is okay then okay.
Or else leave it.

1034
01:01:54,797 --> 01:02:01,402
Stop bothering me.
Okay? Get out. Get out.

1035
01:02:01,672 --> 01:02:04,925
She came in style..

1036
01:02:11,565 --> 01:02:15,317
Why is the police here
without permission? - Do not yell.

1037
01:02:15,476 --> 01:02:17,045
He is come with a warrant.

1038
01:02:17,126 --> 01:02:20,467
Maari's asleep. Come back later.
- Do not yell!

1039
01:02:21,021 --> 01:02:23,972
Do not make a sound or
I will kill you. - Heard that?

1040
01:02:24,052 --> 01:02:25,947
We have got a warrant against you.

1041
01:02:26,250 --> 01:02:28,871
Officer asked me to bring you in.
- Who is the officer?

1042
01:02:42,132 --> 01:02:46,217
I said to wake me up early morning,
I am getting bad dreams.

1043
01:02:46,297 --> 01:02:49,731
Get up. We have come to arrest you.
- Arrest? Why?

1044
01:02:58,293 --> 01:02:59,698
Murder?

1045
01:03:01,188 --> 01:03:05,186
Murder? Something like murder.

1046
01:03:05,266 --> 01:03:07,021
There was this guy called
Pandu in our town.

1047
01:03:07,641 --> 01:03:10,481
Real big shot. Not anyone
could have laid a finger on him.

1048
01:03:10,561 --> 01:03:13,043
One day I just went
and casually stabbed him.

1049
01:03:19,945 --> 01:03:23,300
Give money!
This is how you run a business.

1050
01:03:25,927 --> 01:03:28,157
I can not take this anymore.

1051
01:03:28,347 --> 01:03:30,563
I am going to the police.
- Listen to me, madam.

1052
01:03:30,643 --> 01:03:32,530
It is an unnecessary trouble.
- I do not care.

1053
01:03:32,610 --> 01:03:34,134
I want to meet the sub-inspector.

1054
01:03:34,213 --> 01:03:36,538
Nothing, sir.
It is just a petty case. - Sir..

1055
01:03:36,617 --> 01:03:37,978
Sir, I want to file a complaint
against Maari.

1056
01:03:38,057 --> 01:03:40,297
Nuisance case. File the complaint.

1057
01:03:40,378 --> 01:03:43,852
I am ready to testify anywhere.
- I appreciate your bravery.

1058
01:03:43,931 --> 01:03:47,232
But if I charge him with this small
case then he will come out easily.

1059
01:03:47,313 --> 01:03:49,780
After that he will cause
more trouble for you and me.

1060
01:03:50,288 --> 01:03:52,262
We need to catch
him in a bigger case.

1061
01:03:52,342 --> 01:03:54,500
I will be glad to
help however I can.

1062
01:03:55,318 --> 01:03:56,682
After a lot of searching..

1063
01:03:56,762 --> 01:03:59,864
I have found the
file of a closed case.

1064
01:04:00,369 --> 01:04:02,229
The murder attempt
of a man named Pandu.

1065
01:04:03,070 --> 01:04:04,784
The suspicion's
age and description..

1066
01:04:04,934 --> 01:04:07,966
..fits with Maari.
But that is not enough.

1067
01:04:08,505 --> 01:04:11,021
We need stronger evidence
connecting Maari to the case.

1068
01:04:11,614 --> 01:04:13,916
What can I do for this?

1069
01:04:15,050 --> 01:04:18,079
What would you do?
- I will help you.

1070
01:04:22,244 --> 01:04:24,721
Calling him brother does not
come naturally to me.

1071
01:04:31,072 --> 01:04:32,461
What happened, Maari?

1072
01:04:38,146 --> 01:04:40,756
Be careful!
- Hey!

1073
01:04:40,914 --> 01:04:44,215
Just hangover from last
night's booze. Give that.

1074
01:04:45,137 --> 01:04:49,256
You are disturbing
me early morning.

1075
01:04:50,746 --> 01:04:53,304
Good job, man. Good job.

1076
01:05:00,429 --> 01:05:03,460
I have done lot of hooliganism.

1077
01:05:03,659 --> 01:05:07,674
I broke hands and legs, I did
many things. Nothing happened then.

1078
01:05:07,755 --> 01:05:09,664
For the first time ever..

1079
01:05:10,000 --> 01:05:13,010
I fell in love.
And they are going to lock me up.

1080
01:05:13,235 --> 01:05:15,896
That is the fate.
Fall in love, Maari..

1081
01:05:16,050 --> 01:05:18,278
Fall in love, Maari!
Fall in love, Maari!

1082
01:05:18,481 --> 01:05:20,533
Screwed us, right?

1083
01:05:20,731 --> 01:05:22,994
What are you looking at?
Come, take me away.

1084
01:05:23,552 --> 01:05:26,839
He suggested it but
the girl has accepted it.

1085
01:05:27,012 --> 01:05:29,765
Everyone seems to have developed,
just not us.

1086
01:05:29,844 --> 01:05:32,212
Wait.

1087
01:05:32,786 --> 01:05:35,416
Is it okay? - Little bit
to the right. - Which side?

1088
01:05:35,496 --> 01:05:37,421
Left side. - Okay?
- Perfect.

1089
01:05:41,889 --> 01:05:44,458
Why are they bursting crackers?
Is it a festival day?

1090
01:05:44,762 --> 01:05:48,335
Not a festival, Maari.
The news of your arrest has spread.

1091
01:05:48,416 --> 01:05:50,077
Rascals!

1092
01:05:50,157 --> 01:05:52,931
They do not even burst
crackers for holidays.

1093
01:05:53,010 --> 01:05:55,009
But look at them
celebrating my arrest!

1094
01:05:55,460 --> 01:05:56,582
They have torn it already?

1095
01:05:58,527 --> 01:06:00,191
You guys do not stay here.

1096
01:06:00,271 --> 01:06:02,736
Go away.
They will keep prodding you.

1097
01:06:03,005 --> 01:06:05,997
If a girl comes and says
she loves you, just chase her away.

1098
01:06:06,077 --> 01:06:08,226
We do not have anyone
but you, Maari.

1099
01:06:08,306 --> 01:06:11,358
No one in the area will
respect us now. Tell him.

1100
01:06:11,438 --> 01:06:13,434
Who do we have but you?

1101
01:06:13,967 --> 01:06:18,182
Did not work out. Do not overact.
You uncle lives in Kakinada, right?

1102
01:06:18,262 --> 01:06:19,842
Go.

1103
01:06:29,351 --> 01:06:33,310
You have won. You used a woman,
but you still won.

1104
01:06:33,391 --> 01:06:34,780
When you waltzed into
my area without permission..

1105
01:06:34,860 --> 01:06:35,893
..I should have bumped you off.

1106
01:06:35,974 --> 01:06:37,514
Sparing you was a mistake.

1107
01:06:37,724 --> 01:06:41,566
Where is that girl?
She must be feasting her eyes.

1108
01:06:44,623 --> 01:06:48,039
What an actor you are!

1109
01:06:48,119 --> 01:06:51,094
With all that talking and smiling,
you have finished me, right?

1110
01:06:51,175 --> 01:06:53,714
See her.
- She is ripped me apart, right?

1111
01:06:53,847 --> 01:06:55,909
She trapped you very well.

1112
01:06:57,635 --> 01:06:58,663
Get into the vehicle.

1113
01:06:59,601 --> 01:07:01,161
Will not be nice if we force you in.

1114
01:07:01,240 --> 01:07:03,326
Oh, my dialogue from the other day?

1115
01:07:03,516 --> 01:07:06,051
Good! It was a good counter,
let is go.

1116
01:07:10,519 --> 01:07:11,777
Bye.

1117
01:07:16,992 --> 01:07:18,365
No AC?

1118
01:07:31,023 --> 01:07:33,115
Maari!

1119
01:07:34,916 --> 01:07:36,981
Maari!

1120
01:07:49,617 --> 01:07:52,257
Here comes Maari! Let is go.

1121
01:07:56,818 --> 01:08:00,052
How are you? How are you, Anna?
- I am fine, Maari.

1122
01:08:01,063 --> 01:08:03,902
Thought you would have lost
weight but you are all fat.

1123
01:08:04,561 --> 01:08:05,833
How are you?
- What Maari?

1124
01:08:06,717 --> 01:08:08,715
You have lost so much weight.

1125
01:08:08,795 --> 01:08:10,911
When have I ever been fat?
- Beat like that, brother.

1126
01:08:11,108 --> 01:08:13,083
One tea for Anna!
- Okay, brother.

1127
01:08:13,393 --> 01:08:14,675
So, what is going on, old man?

1128
01:08:15,146 --> 01:08:17,260
With me gone, everyone in
the area must have been at peace?

1129
01:08:18,858 --> 01:08:21,081
No, Maari.
The situation in the area..

1130
01:08:21,698 --> 01:08:23,291
..has become very bad.

1131
01:08:24,305 --> 01:08:26,503
What happened? - They have arrested
Velu Anna and kept him under remand.

1132
01:08:27,061 --> 01:08:30,833
What? - You said it was not safe for
us to be here when you are in jail.

1133
01:08:30,996 --> 01:08:32,507
We went out of town
for a little while.

1134
01:08:32,587 --> 01:08:34,671
When we returned,
the area was unrecognisable.

1135
01:08:34,751 --> 01:08:37,300
That cop did not just
target us for no reason.

1136
01:08:37,541 --> 01:08:40,163
He had his own agenda.
- What?

1137
01:08:40,320 --> 01:08:42,689
They have arrested Maari
and you are just telling me!

1138
01:08:42,829 --> 01:08:44,532
When he was being arrested..

1139
01:08:44,905 --> 01:08:47,590
Start the vehicle.
I want him released today!

1140
01:08:47,670 --> 01:08:49,470
Sir! Sir!

1141
01:08:49,679 --> 01:08:52,605
Sir! Sir..

1142
01:08:52,685 --> 01:08:54,446
Sir.. Please, sir.

1143
01:08:54,884 --> 01:08:57,454
We have got information that
you are smuggling red sanders.

1144
01:08:58,134 --> 01:09:00,666
The Revenue Department
is here with a search warrant.

1145
01:09:00,746 --> 01:09:02,578
Do you know whose place this is?

1146
01:09:02,658 --> 01:09:04,209
Fool, there are cameras.

1147
01:09:05,555 --> 01:09:07,485
How did the media get
here even before searching?

1148
01:09:09,078 --> 01:09:10,208
I do not know, sir.

1149
01:09:10,962 --> 01:09:13,025
Someone must have
leaked information.

1150
01:09:13,105 --> 01:09:14,886
Sir, start the search.

1151
01:09:20,916 --> 01:09:22,846
When Velu Anna got
arrested and put in jail..

1152
01:09:23,106 --> 01:09:25,150
..all the MLA's
supported him backed out.

1153
01:09:25,341 --> 01:09:27,435
There was no one to bail him out.

1154
01:09:27,515 --> 01:09:30,838
Arjun has a solid reputation..

1155
01:09:30,996 --> 01:09:33,123
..at the Department for
busting rowdyism in the area.

1156
01:09:33,408 --> 01:09:34,849
Everyone in the
area was very happy!

1157
01:09:35,014 --> 01:09:37,069
They celebrated that fellow Arjun.

1158
01:09:37,944 --> 01:09:39,872
He came to our area one night.

1159
01:09:40,527 --> 01:09:41,814
He entered with a plan.

1160
01:09:42,006 --> 01:09:45,534
You might have heard about the red
sanders smuggling arrest from last week.

1161
01:09:45,826 --> 01:09:47,908
The Forest Department
has decided to..

1162
01:09:48,073 --> 01:09:50,536
..export the wood legally.

1163
01:09:50,746 --> 01:09:52,497
This job requires immediate labour.

1164
01:09:52,757 --> 01:09:55,873
Thought this would be a good opportunity
for the unemployed in the area.

1165
01:09:56,153 --> 01:09:58,257
If you are interested,
you may sign up for the job.

1166
01:09:58,337 --> 01:10:00,914
Officer Arjun has come
up with this. We can trust him.

1167
01:10:00,994 --> 01:10:04,947
Let is sign up. - You have received
an invitation to get a job!

1168
01:10:05,198 --> 01:10:07,062
Go sign up.

1169
01:10:07,229 --> 01:10:09,895
You too come, we will
go and sign up. - Sir, sir..

1170
01:10:10,323 --> 01:10:12,187
This will not suit me at all.

1171
01:10:25,652 --> 01:10:28,675
Both red sanders and ordinary
wooden logs are stacked here.

1172
01:10:28,952 --> 01:10:31,920
One load of each needs to be..

1173
01:10:32,000 --> 01:10:34,369
..loaded in the
lorries That is the job.

1174
01:10:45,373 --> 01:10:48,097
The people asked no questions
and continued to work this way.

1175
01:10:48,738 --> 01:10:51,554
This went on for two, three days.

1176
01:10:52,237 --> 01:10:53,862
One day, Arjun..

1177
01:10:53,942 --> 01:10:55,512
..did not turn up at the yard.

1178
01:10:57,048 --> 01:10:58,735
There was a raid that night.

1179
01:11:05,945 --> 01:11:07,945
Seize the goods and make a report.

1180
01:11:08,025 --> 01:11:10,599
Stop the labourers.
No one shall escape. - Yes, sir.

1181
01:11:10,680 --> 01:11:12,942
Sir, this is taking place with
government's permission. - Yes.

1182
01:11:13,021 --> 01:11:15,471
A government job taking place
all hushed up in a closed mill?

1183
01:11:15,551 --> 01:11:16,989
Sir, something is wrong.

1184
01:11:17,069 --> 01:11:19,864
You may call Officer Arjun.
He is the one who got us these jobs.

1185
01:11:19,944 --> 01:11:22,036
We went straight to him
after finding this place.

1186
01:11:22,175 --> 01:11:23,552
He asked us to make the arrests.

1187
01:11:23,632 --> 01:11:25,742
Just get in the jeep!
- Sir! Sir!

1188
01:11:25,823 --> 01:11:29,099
Sir! Sir! Leave!

1189
01:11:29,179 --> 01:11:31,453
Just get in the jeep!

1190
01:11:32,150 --> 01:11:34,246
Why is he running like this?

1191
01:11:34,327 --> 01:11:36,724
The people who had signed
up for transporting the wood..

1192
01:11:36,804 --> 01:11:39,416
They have been arrested and
taken in with charges of smuggling.

1193
01:11:39,670 --> 01:11:41,021
What are you saying?

1194
01:11:41,101 --> 01:11:43,720
Officer Arjun had taken them for
the job. Did you tell him about it?

1195
01:11:43,801 --> 01:11:46,963
I went to the station. They
said he has taken two days off.

1196
01:11:47,042 --> 01:11:50,989
The next day,
strange things began to happen.

1197
01:11:52,243 --> 01:11:54,344
Listen up, everybody!

1198
01:11:54,497 --> 01:11:57,214
All the shops in the market place
are under Ravi Anna's control now.

1199
01:11:57,418 --> 01:12:00,493
You had better pay up on time..

1200
01:12:00,573 --> 01:12:02,346
..if you want to your
shops to remain. - Hey!

1201
01:12:02,488 --> 01:12:05,687
Even Maari is gone now. Who are
you to collect from us? - Exactly!

1202
01:12:05,768 --> 01:12:08,394
Want to see what would happen
if Officer Arjun finds out?

1203
01:12:24,680 --> 01:12:27,536
You were right! I had to see what
would happen if Arjun finds out.

1204
01:12:27,615 --> 01:12:31,091
Anyone else has something to say?

1205
01:12:32,005 --> 01:12:36,282
I shall never hear
Maari's name again.

1206
01:12:36,703 --> 01:12:39,057
Whatever I say will be the law.

1207
01:12:39,337 --> 01:12:41,006
That is when we found
out the real matter.

1208
01:12:41,087 --> 01:12:43,773
This cop and "Bird" Ravi
were in it together the whole time!

1209
01:12:43,853 --> 01:12:46,488
Sir, we sent our men to
work only because of your word.

1210
01:12:46,568 --> 01:12:48,271
Now they are saying
something about smuggling!

1211
01:12:48,350 --> 01:12:51,057
Yes. I did take them
for a smuggling job.

1212
01:12:51,363 --> 01:12:53,472
Ravi and I did all this together.

1213
01:12:54,131 --> 01:12:56,875
If I had told you smuggling
then would not have come to work.

1214
01:12:56,954 --> 01:12:59,390
We were just trying it for the first time.
There was a small goof up.

1215
01:12:59,470 --> 01:13:01,052
And there was a raid, too!

1216
01:13:01,132 --> 01:13:04,969
Sir, testify that they did not know what
the job was. And get them released, sir.

1217
01:13:05,048 --> 01:13:07,737
Are you stupid?
Then I wll get caught.

1218
01:13:07,817 --> 01:13:09,514
No way. Just leave.
- Sir. - Sir..

1219
01:13:09,594 --> 01:13:11,907
Sir, I helped you because
I thought you were a good guy.

1220
01:13:11,987 --> 01:13:14,872
How could you listen to
them and do such terrible things?

1221
01:13:14,952 --> 01:13:16,307
Listen to them?

1222
01:13:16,497 --> 01:13:20,598
This was all my idea. Do you know
why we got Maari arrested?

1223
01:13:20,679 --> 01:13:23,695
To take their places.

1224
01:13:23,775 --> 01:13:27,617
This is why I re-opened
Maari's old case.

1225
01:13:28,854 --> 01:13:31,668
You stopped being of
use after Maari's arrest.

1226
01:13:32,055 --> 01:13:33,953
Do not ask unnecessary questions.
Mind your business.

1227
01:13:34,033 --> 01:13:35,914
No. I will not let this go.

1228
01:13:35,994 --> 01:13:38,282
What will you do, woman?

1229
01:13:38,363 --> 01:13:40,199
Sir, this is wrong.

1230
01:13:40,279 --> 01:13:42,782
Hanumanth, chase them away.
- Sir..

1231
01:13:43,155 --> 01:13:45,345
What are you staring at?
- Poor people.

1232
01:13:45,682 --> 01:13:49,029
Let is get them out somehow!
- Listen, just do as I say.

1233
01:13:49,293 --> 01:13:50,506
Everybody, leave.

1234
01:13:51,347 --> 01:13:56,079
Their plan was to arrest you and
Velu Anna and smuggle red sanders.

1235
01:13:59,060 --> 01:14:02,019
Leave! Move!

1236
01:14:10,509 --> 01:14:12,587
"Bird" Ravi's controls..

1237
01:14:12,667 --> 01:14:14,626
..Pigeon race and tournaments.

1238
01:14:14,815 --> 01:14:16,518
There is no ethics.

1239
01:14:16,658 --> 01:14:19,997
It is terrible. They just
do everything to their convenience.

1240
01:14:20,194 --> 01:14:23,488
Most of the pro fanciers
have stopped racing.

1241
01:14:31,820 --> 01:14:34,682
Cheers!

1242
01:14:35,069 --> 01:14:38,820
I got word from Velu
Anna after your release.

1243
01:14:38,900 --> 01:14:42,782
He said to leave the area.
That it will be better to vacate.

1244
01:14:46,095 --> 01:14:48,445
Let is leave.
- Why did you say like that, Maari?

1245
01:14:48,632 --> 01:14:49,877
What else should I say?

1246
01:14:50,345 --> 01:14:53,858
Velu Anna has said so himself.
Who do we stay back for?

1247
01:14:54,609 --> 01:14:56,045
Bring the pigeons and everything.

1248
01:14:56,126 --> 01:14:57,547
Let is leave.

1249
01:14:58,416 --> 01:15:00,788
Sannasi, you heard him.

1250
01:15:00,989 --> 01:15:03,015
Pack our stuff and
bring the vehicle.

1251
01:15:03,137 --> 01:15:04,664
We will not visit that area again.

1252
01:15:07,162 --> 01:15:09,411
Why are they loading things?
- I do not know!

1253
01:15:09,490 --> 01:15:12,685
You useless,
bring it carefully. - What?

1254
01:15:12,837 --> 01:15:14,650
Where are you going?

1255
01:15:15,625 --> 01:15:16,797
Has Maari been released?

1256
01:15:17,301 --> 01:15:19,463
Is he here, too?
- Tell me! - Are you blind?

1257
01:15:19,543 --> 01:15:20,600
We are just leaving.

1258
01:15:22,202 --> 01:15:24,735
We wll never come by here.
You can be happy. - Hold it.

1259
01:15:26,354 --> 01:15:28,116
It is so hard to
leave our birthplace!

1260
01:15:28,197 --> 01:15:30,291
Look, it is hard for us, too.

1261
01:15:30,371 --> 01:15:33,216
You deserve it!
You played the fiddle to that cop.

1262
01:15:33,465 --> 01:15:37,307
We wll do our jobs elsewhere.
People will spit on you later.

1263
01:15:42,533 --> 01:15:44,692
Look who else is here

1264
01:15:44,773 --> 01:15:47,668
They are leaving with
their belongings. - Sannasi!

1265
01:15:47,903 --> 01:15:50,369
Is notyour Anna Maari here?
- How will he come?

1266
01:15:50,448 --> 01:15:52,023
How could he ever
face anyone in the area?

1267
01:15:52,104 --> 01:15:54,405
Look, do not show off
after doing stupid things.

1268
01:15:54,796 --> 01:15:57,776
You are not fit to compete
with Anna. Leave! Leave!

1269
01:15:57,904 --> 01:15:59,813
What qualification do we need?
What qualification do we need?

1270
01:15:59,893 --> 01:16:01,407
Do not do it I say!

1271
01:16:01,487 --> 01:16:04,298
Go ahead and do it. He can
take a beating. - Yes, he can.

1272
01:16:04,518 --> 01:16:06,811
Maari hits you everyday.

1273
01:16:07,055 --> 01:16:08,694
Let us hit you today.

1274
01:16:08,842 --> 01:16:10,037
Hit him!

1275
01:16:10,117 --> 01:16:11,914
I will hit you
and you will take it.

1276
01:16:12,225 --> 01:16:13,606
He was leaving anyway.

1277
01:16:13,685 --> 01:16:17,985
Old man! - What is this?
- Hey, let him go!

1278
01:16:18,320 --> 01:16:21,220
Hey! You!

1279
01:16:56,822 --> 01:16:59,900
Maari!

1280
01:17:01,029 --> 01:17:03,911
Come.
- You will go to him?

1281
01:17:53,591 --> 01:17:54,816
Maari!

1282
01:17:57,360 --> 01:17:59,140
Do not do it, Maari! Do not!

1283
01:18:09,385 --> 01:18:12,057
Hey, dummy!
Looks like your face is poached.

1284
01:18:12,279 --> 01:18:14,295
Cheekiness is bad.

1285
01:18:55,686 --> 01:18:57,923
"Maari is back!"

1286
01:18:58,360 --> 01:19:00,519
"Maari is a fireball."

1287
01:19:01,042 --> 01:19:03,319
"Bigger and better."

1288
01:19:03,787 --> 01:19:07,072
"Take to your heels."

1289
01:19:15,563 --> 01:19:21,440
"Your face will get mangled, eyes
removed, shape beyond recognition."

1290
01:19:21,520 --> 01:19:26,938
"Maari is back! Maari is a fireball!
He will cross all his limits."

1291
01:19:30,912 --> 01:19:32,320
"That is Maari."

1292
01:19:35,859 --> 01:19:37,804
"That is Maari."

1293
01:19:39,988 --> 01:19:42,835
Go. Go and tell the cop.

1294
01:19:44,042 --> 01:19:45,895
I will be here.

1295
01:19:46,047 --> 01:19:47,881
He may have the area
under his control.

1296
01:19:48,204 --> 01:19:50,820
But Maari is always out of control.

1297
01:19:54,323 --> 01:19:56,456
Only I get to beat him up.

1298
01:19:57,242 --> 01:20:00,079
Think you get to
show off in my area?

1299
01:20:02,117 --> 01:20:03,125
I wll finish you off!

1300
01:20:32,225 --> 01:20:34,073
Stop! What are you doing here?

1301
01:20:34,154 --> 01:20:35,572
Maari does not want
to see your faces.

1302
01:20:35,652 --> 01:20:39,298
Go away. - Get out of my way!
We want to talk to our man Maari.

1303
01:20:39,378 --> 01:20:41,358
Your man Maari? - Do not
you understand when we tell?

1304
01:20:41,506 --> 01:20:43,675
Maari, things got really
rough in your absence.

1305
01:20:43,755 --> 01:20:45,731
That cop tricked us and..

1306
01:20:45,811 --> 01:20:47,899
..got us in trouble.
- Not just that..

1307
01:20:47,979 --> 01:20:49,409
..he is hiked the bribe threefold.

1308
01:20:49,489 --> 01:20:51,997
None of us can live!
- Drop dead, then. - Yes, Maari.

1309
01:20:52,078 --> 01:20:53,858
We were really scared and helpless.

1310
01:20:53,938 --> 01:20:56,365
We wll be brave
now that you are here.

1311
01:20:58,635 --> 01:20:59,884
Hey, you..

1312
01:20:59,963 --> 01:21:02,345
You are the ones who
burst crackers and..

1313
01:21:02,426 --> 01:21:03,875
..celebrated my arrest!

1314
01:21:03,954 --> 01:21:06,163
This wash-basin face was
the one who fired a flower-pot.

1315
01:21:07,612 --> 01:21:10,280
You people chose to
be allied to that cop.

1316
01:21:10,940 --> 01:21:11,978
Suffer, now.

1317
01:21:13,582 --> 01:21:14,633
Go away!

1318
01:21:14,712 --> 01:21:18,881
Maari! - Leave! Leave!
Maari Anna told you. - Leave!

1319
01:21:32,502 --> 01:21:33,525
Are you stupid?

1320
01:21:33,762 --> 01:21:35,947
He would have left on his own.

1321
01:21:36,389 --> 01:21:38,907
Now you picked a fight
with him and made him stay back.

1322
01:21:40,119 --> 01:21:41,826
What could he do here, anyway?

1323
01:21:43,233 --> 01:21:44,965
We shall corner him..

1324
01:21:45,824 --> 01:21:47,393
..at the right time and place.

1325
01:21:49,398 --> 01:21:51,791
Check if all the pigeons
are in the right condition.

1326
01:21:52,000 --> 01:21:54,373
I wll come and check on
the young birds in the morning.

1327
01:21:54,989 --> 01:21:57,469
We wll start the training
tomorrow morning.

1328
01:21:57,550 --> 01:22:02,149
Okay, Maari. - Okay?
- How dare you come back again?

1329
01:22:02,229 --> 01:22:03,926
I came to say sorry.

1330
01:22:04,466 --> 01:22:05,588
I am sorry.

1331
01:22:06,128 --> 01:22:09,568
I know you must
be very angry with me.

1332
01:22:09,911 --> 01:22:13,243
But I did have my reasons.

1333
01:22:13,323 --> 01:22:15,222
I thought I was
doing the right thing.

1334
01:22:15,475 --> 01:22:18,339
I did not realise I was helping..

1335
01:22:18,835 --> 01:22:20,326
..the bad guy.

1336
01:22:20,859 --> 01:22:23,252
Anyhow, it is wrong to betray..

1337
01:22:23,462 --> 01:22:26,374
..someone's trust in any situation.

1338
01:22:26,837 --> 01:22:28,722
So, I am really sorry.

1339
01:22:31,104 --> 01:22:33,300
I have come all the way to apologise!

1340
01:22:33,591 --> 01:22:36,257
Will not you at least respond to me?

1341
01:22:39,805 --> 01:22:41,207
I forgive you. Leave.

1342
01:22:48,158 --> 01:22:50,595
Go, go.

1343
01:22:51,525 --> 01:22:53,886
Maari asked you to leave! Leave.

1344
01:22:59,110 --> 01:23:00,559
Do you know why Maari
committed that murder?

1345
01:23:00,639 --> 01:23:03,288
Because they killed
his loved pigeon.

1346
01:23:03,586 --> 01:23:05,458
Tell me honestly.

1347
01:23:05,693 --> 01:23:08,351
If you had been in his place, would not you
be furious? Would not you do anything?

1348
01:23:09,030 --> 01:23:11,747
Why do you trouble the area people?

1349
01:23:11,828 --> 01:23:13,591
Why can not you show
the affection on people..

1350
01:23:13,671 --> 01:23:16,279
..that you bestow upon pigeons?
- Why should we?

1351
01:23:16,412 --> 01:23:17,967
To these people?

1352
01:23:18,119 --> 01:23:19,644
Did they do that for Maari?

1353
01:23:20,837 --> 01:23:22,805
Who helped him when he was a kid?

1354
01:23:23,536 --> 01:23:26,006
When he was alone and hungry?
Who helped him then?

1355
01:23:26,640 --> 01:23:27,859
Not one person came.

1356
01:23:28,202 --> 01:23:30,118
He only had one thing then.

1357
01:23:30,198 --> 01:23:31,457
His pigeons.

1358
01:23:31,537 --> 01:23:33,152
It was the pigeons that fed him.

1359
01:23:33,231 --> 01:23:35,904
Maari always says..

1360
01:23:36,127 --> 01:23:37,878
..you can trust a pigeon..

1361
01:23:37,958 --> 01:23:41,186
..but not a human.
Now you have proved him right.

1362
01:23:41,266 --> 01:23:44,195
What I did seemed right that day.

1363
01:23:44,275 --> 01:23:45,711
Do not you talk about
right and wrong!

1364
01:23:45,845 --> 01:23:47,559
Have you ever struggled in life?

1365
01:23:47,639 --> 01:23:49,000
Have you ever struggled
for a daily meal?

1366
01:23:49,158 --> 01:23:50,445
If you just waltz
in here and apologise..

1367
01:23:50,525 --> 01:23:52,161
..think he wll grin and accept?

1368
01:23:52,240 --> 01:23:55,487
Look, he does not ever want to set
eyes on you after what you have done.

1369
01:23:55,645 --> 01:23:57,517
If you keep coming back here..

1370
01:23:57,853 --> 01:23:59,262
..it will get rough.

1371
01:23:59,877 --> 01:24:01,851
Stop talking to her. Let is leave.

1372
01:24:20,605 --> 01:24:22,452
What is your problem?

1373
01:24:24,235 --> 01:24:26,305
Tell me, or buzz off!

1374
01:24:26,502 --> 01:24:31,104
A few days after you went to
the jail, my school fees was due.

1375
01:24:31,184 --> 01:24:35,047
But it was not paid at all.
After that my school staff said..

1376
01:24:35,127 --> 01:24:38,431
..you were paying my fees.

1377
01:24:41,280 --> 01:24:42,311
I was not paying.

1378
01:24:42,391 --> 01:24:45,523
I know you are paying
without anybody's knowledge.

1379
01:24:45,701 --> 01:24:48,126
It is okay, I will not tell anybody.

1380
01:24:48,206 --> 01:24:50,595
Did not I say that I have not paid?

1381
01:24:50,867 --> 01:24:53,559
What do I care if
you go to school? Leave.

1382
01:24:55,076 --> 01:24:59,024
Did that cop trick you and
jail you?

1383
01:25:03,962 --> 01:25:06,309
Did they hit you in the jail?

1384
01:25:08,283 --> 01:25:10,131
Did you suffer?

1385
01:25:12,519 --> 01:25:13,979
Poor thing.

1386
01:25:15,264 --> 01:25:16,788
It was not that bad. Go, now!

1387
01:25:16,953 --> 01:25:19,822
I was not talking about you.
I meant the cop.

1388
01:25:19,902 --> 01:25:22,524
You wll get him, one fine day!

1389
01:25:32,076 --> 01:25:33,965
Loudmouth, go to sleep.

1390
01:25:34,045 --> 01:25:35,427
Rogue!

1391
01:25:45,514 --> 01:25:47,243
We can enter our birds
to the race next week.

1392
01:25:47,323 --> 01:25:48,780
All the pigeons are ready.

1393
01:25:48,963 --> 01:25:51,327
Our next target is Arjun.

1394
01:25:51,676 --> 01:25:54,579
Do not know why, but my hands
feel all jittery since morning.

1395
01:25:54,659 --> 01:25:55,764
What?
- No!

1396
01:25:55,844 --> 01:25:58,604
Need to do something about
this Arjun and "Bird Ravi".

1397
01:25:58,684 --> 01:26:02,030
He is a cop.
You can not do him on urgent basis.

1398
01:26:02,110 --> 01:26:04,046
Must keep calm.

1399
01:26:05,869 --> 01:26:08,725
I am idle nowadays.
Feeling a little lazy.

1400
01:26:09,051 --> 01:26:15,947
I am so bored. I want to some job.
- Job?

1401
01:26:16,176 --> 01:26:19,119
Oh Jesus! Save this Child.

1402
01:26:19,643 --> 01:26:20,801
What?

1403
01:26:21,746 --> 01:26:23,697
Did you have a job before all this?

1404
01:26:23,777 --> 01:26:26,623
We were breaking a few bones,
causing trouble!

1405
01:26:26,703 --> 01:26:29,467
Collecting racketeering money
and we even raced pigeons.

1406
01:26:29,547 --> 01:26:30,710
Is that a job, Anna?

1407
01:26:30,789 --> 01:26:34,310
You have been acting cocky ever
since I returned from the jail.

1408
01:26:34,390 --> 01:26:37,903
Not for me. What job can you do?
- I wll do any job! - Any job?

1409
01:26:37,983 --> 01:26:39,284
I wll do any job!

1410
01:26:39,363 --> 01:26:41,823
So we wll get you a
painting job with Murali?

1411
01:26:41,904 --> 01:26:45,079
But painting is an artist's job.

1412
01:26:45,158 --> 01:26:46,193
I can not do that!

1413
01:26:46,274 --> 01:26:47,901
You paint the place red
when you hit people.

1414
01:26:47,980 --> 01:26:50,318
But that is not the same, idiot!

1415
01:26:50,399 --> 01:26:51,947
There is a mechanic in our area.
Mani.

1416
01:26:52,027 --> 01:26:53,886
You can chase him
out and do his job.

1417
01:26:53,966 --> 01:26:57,251
Chasing out part, I can do..
but mechanic's work..

1418
01:26:57,331 --> 01:26:58,951
But I do not know about unscrewing,
screwing and all that.

1419
01:26:59,030 --> 01:27:00,202
You said you wll do any job!

1420
01:27:00,282 --> 01:27:02,333
You are only naming
jobs that I can not do.

1421
01:27:02,676 --> 01:27:05,481
Remember sister Rani? We
seized an auto from her husband..

1422
01:27:05,561 --> 01:27:07,582
..when he failed to pay up.
That auto is still with us.

1423
01:27:09,354 --> 01:27:12,806
That is correct! - We wll dismantle
and sell the parts? - No!

1424
01:27:12,984 --> 01:27:14,259
We wll drive the auto!

1425
01:27:14,340 --> 01:27:16,641
Just talking about it will not do!
You need to know how to ride one.

1426
01:27:18,819 --> 01:27:19,942
Come here.

1427
01:27:20,266 --> 01:27:23,162
You never game me so much respect.
- I will tell. Come and sit.

1428
01:27:23,243 --> 01:27:25,010
Tell me. -Sit down!

1429
01:27:25,731 --> 01:27:28,302
What is the matter?
- The auto..

1430
01:27:28,461 --> 01:27:30,533
You are mocking me?

1431
01:27:30,690 --> 01:27:32,323
Auto.. you can drive.

1432
01:27:32,634 --> 01:27:36,060
Say something.
- Shall we? - You can drive.

1433
01:27:36,331 --> 01:27:38,672
So are driving auto drive tomorrow.

1434
01:28:02,927 --> 01:28:08,166
Super, Maari! You go. Be careful.
- Sit in the auto. - It is okay. - Get in!

1435
01:28:08,375 --> 01:28:09,695
Get in!
- You too come.

1436
01:28:10,329 --> 01:28:13,353
Get in! Get in!

1437
01:28:14,989 --> 01:28:16,945
This is strange!

1438
01:28:27,572 --> 01:28:29,087
Want to take the auto?

1439
01:28:29,238 --> 01:28:31,173
No, Anna. - Where are you headed?
- Dhaba Gardens.

1440
01:28:31,371 --> 01:28:34,371
Will not take the auto to Dhaba Gardens?
- I will take the bus. - Get in.

1441
01:28:34,451 --> 01:28:37,149
No, Anna. - Get in. - There
is a graveyard nearby. - Get in.

1442
01:28:37,814 --> 01:28:41,440
Get in! - Anna! - Right!

1443
01:28:53,413 --> 01:28:55,032
Stop it!

1444
01:28:55,654 --> 01:28:57,121
Give us the amount.

1445
01:28:58,130 --> 01:28:59,983
How much, Anna?
- Just give me that! - Anna.

1446
01:29:00,063 --> 01:29:01,399
Anna! Anna! - Leave!

1447
01:29:01,690 --> 01:29:04,273
Please be generous.
- Okay, carry on.

1448
01:29:05,518 --> 01:29:08,425
Anna! - Stop!

1449
01:29:08,823 --> 01:29:11,757
Get in... go sit inside.

1450
01:29:11,837 --> 01:29:13,827
Get in.

1451
01:29:14,367 --> 01:29:16,207
Auto, huh?
- Of course it is an auto.

1452
01:29:16,287 --> 01:29:18,092
Get in.

1453
01:29:18,172 --> 01:29:21,579
Sir, I have come on my bike.
- I said get in. - Maari.

1454
01:29:21,659 --> 01:29:24,461
Get in I say! - Sir, sir..

1455
01:29:24,786 --> 01:29:27,737
Get in I say! Will not you listen!

1456
01:29:27,817 --> 01:29:30,134
Squeeze in! Push in!

1457
01:29:30,672 --> 01:29:32,822
Stop! He wants to ride
in some other auto!

1458
01:29:32,902 --> 01:29:34,266
What are you doing?
- Anna! - Get down!

1459
01:29:34,346 --> 01:29:37,826
Get in! - Anna.. - Get in I say!

1460
01:29:38,663 --> 01:29:41,367
Keep going, do not stop!

1461
01:29:44,756 --> 01:29:47,105
Maari, they are refusing
to accept our entry.

1462
01:29:47,185 --> 01:29:48,724
Have a word with them.

1463
01:29:50,233 --> 01:29:53,769
The entry time is up, Maari. They have
said not to accept any more entries.

1464
01:29:53,947 --> 01:29:57,074
That is not a big deal at all. Call
Murthy Anna. We wll talk to him.

1465
01:29:57,154 --> 01:29:58,814
He is not the current president.

1466
01:29:59,131 --> 01:30:02,280
If you want to register after
the last date, talk to the new president.

1467
01:30:02,360 --> 01:30:04,989
Here he comes. Talk to him.

1468
01:30:05,069 --> 01:30:07,282
Greetings.
- Greetings. - Greetings.

1469
01:30:10,125 --> 01:30:12,650
Hello, Maari.
You have come to register?

1470
01:30:12,730 --> 01:30:14,054
The last date is over.

1471
01:30:14,134 --> 01:30:17,126
You should have come sooner.
Oh, I am sorry!

1472
01:30:17,323 --> 01:30:19,306
You were in the jail, right?
Okay, okay.

1473
01:30:19,386 --> 01:30:22,085
What do we do?
- I do not know, sir.

1474
01:30:22,164 --> 01:30:26,613
I said there is a chance if
they request you. - That is true.

1475
01:30:26,778 --> 01:30:29,139
Ask them to request, then.
- Request?

1476
01:30:29,219 --> 01:30:32,179
This dirty face? - Hey!
- Maari, we wll see next year.

1477
01:30:32,319 --> 01:30:35,498
Shani, do not play up.
- I am saying it openly.

1478
01:30:35,578 --> 01:30:37,383
It is our turn in this area now.

1479
01:30:40,886 --> 01:30:44,034
Are you flying your birds
this year, "Bird" Ravi? - Yes.

1480
01:30:46,520 --> 01:30:50,383
Okay, that is nice.
- What are you grinning for?

1481
01:30:50,804 --> 01:30:52,161
That is nothing. Forget about it.

1482
01:30:52,240 --> 01:30:54,890
I asked you why you were grinning!

1483
01:30:56,190 --> 01:30:57,586
Look at that board.

1484
01:31:00,103 --> 01:31:02,515
You must wish to see
your name there, sometime.

1485
01:31:02,595 --> 01:31:04,855
That is not possible if I compete.
So go ahead.

1486
01:31:04,935 --> 01:31:07,490
You think I can not
compete with your birds?

1487
01:31:08,398 --> 01:31:11,342
The whole world knows that.
Raising your voice will not change it.

1488
01:31:12,097 --> 01:31:13,860
We wll let you win this time.

1489
01:31:13,940 --> 01:31:15,619
Hey!

1490
01:31:16,153 --> 01:31:17,421
Take his entry.

1491
01:31:17,501 --> 01:31:19,453
We wll see who wins.

1492
01:31:19,533 --> 01:31:23,173
No, I wll let you have it this time.
- You are competing.

1493
01:31:23,387 --> 01:31:24,899
Come.

1494
01:31:27,381 --> 01:31:29,463
Why is he requesting
so much? - Yes.

1495
01:31:29,543 --> 01:31:31,894
You heard the President.
Take our entry!

1496
01:31:36,350 --> 01:31:39,251
We prevented him from participating
so that you could win.

1497
01:31:39,331 --> 01:31:40,672
He knew you would fall for it..

1498
01:31:40,752 --> 01:31:43,625
..if he teased you.
And you fell for it!

1499
01:31:43,704 --> 01:31:45,063
You only gave him entry.

1500
01:31:45,143 --> 01:31:46,525
Let it be.

1501
01:31:46,605 --> 01:31:48,702
His pigeons are three
months behind ours in training.

1502
01:31:48,783 --> 01:31:51,859
He does not have any money to feed
them special food and medicines.

1503
01:31:51,939 --> 01:31:55,369
We have readied our pigeons
with imported medicines and tonics.

1504
01:31:55,534 --> 01:31:57,322
We have been training
them for four months!

1505
01:31:57,403 --> 01:31:58,985
This year is ours.

1506
01:31:59,065 --> 01:32:01,367
You have been doing
all this for years now.

1507
01:32:02,185 --> 01:32:04,134
Why have you never won?

1508
01:32:05,773 --> 01:32:08,699
You can not win unless you
admit the opponent's strengths.

1509
01:32:08,779 --> 01:32:10,736
Even if he starts
training them late..

1510
01:32:11,173 --> 01:32:14,024
..even if he trains them with
just water. His pigeons will win.

1511
01:32:14,242 --> 01:32:17,810
That is Maari. That is why
I told you not to let him enter.

1512
01:32:17,975 --> 01:32:21,035
What do you even
know about pigeons?

1513
01:32:22,130 --> 01:32:23,440
Wait and watch.

1514
01:32:23,922 --> 01:32:25,429
As the race day draws closer..

1515
01:32:25,510 --> 01:32:28,364
..you wll get nervous
and ask me for help.

1516
01:32:28,613 --> 01:32:30,212
It will happen.

1517
01:32:32,445 --> 01:32:36,975
Do not stare at the pigeon after
feeding it. He can not digest his food.

1518
01:32:37,725 --> 01:32:41,426
Anna, you told them to train them.
Pigeons are ready.

1519
01:32:42,195 --> 01:32:44,849
Anna.. - Hey..
Why are you hitting him?

1520
01:32:45,248 --> 01:32:47,622
He asked me not to come.
But I came anyway.

1521
01:32:48,162 --> 01:32:50,530
You do good to others
secretly, right?

1522
01:32:50,728 --> 01:32:53,336
You have been paying
Kavitha's school fees..

1523
01:32:53,742 --> 01:32:55,664
..without anybody's knowledge.

1524
01:32:55,944 --> 01:32:59,008
Who? Our Loudspeaker Kavitha?
You never told us!

1525
01:33:00,436 --> 01:33:02,173
Why do you refuse to reveal..

1526
01:33:02,435 --> 01:33:04,603
..the good in you?

1527
01:33:04,784 --> 01:33:06,711
It is fine if you
do not want to accept.

1528
01:33:07,728 --> 01:33:12,432
I knew there is a good guy in there,
somewhere.

1529
01:33:13,028 --> 01:33:14,646
Now I have seen that.

1530
01:33:14,860 --> 01:33:18,105
And that is enough.
Even if you keep chasing me away..

1531
01:33:18,304 --> 01:33:20,333
..I wll keep coming back to help.

1532
01:33:24,158 --> 01:33:26,664
You have helped me enough, already.

1533
01:33:26,814 --> 01:33:29,234
What are you trying to get from me,
by fawning this way?

1534
01:33:29,626 --> 01:33:32,369
Why do you like it
so much to be a bad guy?

1535
01:33:32,893 --> 01:33:34,797
I had rather be a pure bad guy..

1536
01:33:34,877 --> 01:33:36,646
..than an adulterated good guy.

1537
01:33:46,225 --> 01:33:48,845
Ask the street vendors to pay up.

1538
01:33:49,613 --> 01:33:51,613
Do not leave out anyone.

1539
01:33:51,873 --> 01:33:54,417
Pay up! Quickly!

1540
01:33:55,103 --> 01:33:57,546
Pay.
- Here.

1541
01:33:58,523 --> 01:34:02,519
Greetings, Anna. - Take it out.
What are you staring at?

1542
01:34:02,891 --> 01:34:04,898
What a measly amount!

1543
01:34:07,207 --> 01:34:13,055
Have all the auto drivers paid up?
- Yes, all of them but he did not pay.

1544
01:34:17,306 --> 01:34:20,568
Since when does
Maari drive an auto?

1545
01:34:20,797 --> 01:34:23,724
Why has not he paid?
He refuses to join the union.

1546
01:34:23,923 --> 01:34:26,096
He refused and you accepted?

1547
01:34:26,756 --> 01:34:28,907
Pay up, man.

1548
01:34:31,152 --> 01:34:34,438
Pay up nicely or we wll make you.

1549
01:35:03,228 --> 01:35:04,381
Hey..

1550
01:35:13,457 --> 01:35:14,789
Go.

1551
01:35:15,277 --> 01:35:17,145
Go!

1552
01:35:19,470 --> 01:35:21,914
"Maari is back!"

1553
01:35:22,222 --> 01:35:24,389
"Maari is a fireball."

1554
01:35:24,872 --> 01:35:27,151
"Now he is back.
Bigger and better."

1555
01:35:27,635 --> 01:35:31,302
"Better take to your heels."

1556
01:35:35,155 --> 01:35:36,862
You wll take it?

1557
01:35:37,978 --> 01:35:40,038
Will you take it and
reach home in a piece?

1558
01:35:40,118 --> 01:35:45,450
"Your face will get mangled, eyes
removed, shape beyond recognition."

1559
01:35:45,529 --> 01:35:48,307
Bloody bugger!

1560
01:35:48,387 --> 01:35:50,934
"He will cross all his limits."

1561
01:35:54,520 --> 01:35:56,360
Hello!
- That is Maari.

1562
01:35:56,440 --> 01:35:59,597
How much?
- No, it is fine.

1563
01:35:59,677 --> 01:36:01,247
"That is Maari."

1564
01:36:02,238 --> 01:36:04,083
"Maari is back!"

1565
01:36:04,922 --> 01:36:06,905
"Maari is a fireball."

1566
01:36:07,618 --> 01:36:09,764
"He is back!"

1567
01:36:10,284 --> 01:36:12,027
"Take to your heels."

1568
01:36:12,304 --> 01:36:13,787
Maari..

1569
01:36:14,220 --> 01:36:17,100
Still scared of him?

1570
01:36:17,346 --> 01:36:20,045
You should have beat him
up and collected the money.

1571
01:36:20,125 --> 01:36:22,877
Easy for you to say.
We are the one who got beat up.

1572
01:36:23,512 --> 01:36:25,125
It is nothing, sir.

1573
01:36:25,204 --> 01:36:27,497
Let it go. Does not matter
if one guy does not pay.

1574
01:36:28,096 --> 01:36:30,306
Why do you think we collect?

1575
01:36:30,615 --> 01:36:32,217
Is it a major source of income?

1576
01:36:32,463 --> 01:36:34,304
Even they are struggling to pay us.

1577
01:36:34,836 --> 01:36:36,703
We are collecting to..

1578
01:36:36,783 --> 01:36:38,463
..keep them under control.

1579
01:36:38,828 --> 01:36:40,081
Even if one person refuses to pay..

1580
01:36:40,161 --> 01:36:43,134
..that fear will subside.
Can not let that happen.

1581
01:36:43,579 --> 01:36:45,260
Need to fix it tomorrow!

1582
01:36:45,470 --> 01:36:49,347
The chains were a lot heavier
before I went to prison.

1583
01:36:50,365 --> 01:36:51,862
Now it is all light.

1584
01:36:52,007 --> 01:36:55,269
He was roaming around with them!
- Roaming? - I had it in my house, man.

1585
01:36:55,930 --> 01:36:59,046
Maari is the most bejewelled
auto driver in this area.

1586
01:36:59,126 --> 01:37:00,909
Anna, look who is here.

1587
01:37:05,171 --> 01:37:09,177
Maari drives an auto?

1588
01:37:09,256 --> 01:37:14,657
I was expecting complaints that he is
doing rowdyism and causing trouble.

1589
01:37:14,738 --> 01:37:16,673
But he is just driving an auto?

1590
01:37:17,148 --> 01:37:20,552
What is it, Maari?
Heard you refused to pay the fee?

1591
01:37:20,711 --> 01:37:23,615
Caught up in the past, were you?

1592
01:37:23,939 --> 01:37:26,105
You are a nobody now.

1593
01:37:26,257 --> 01:37:28,367
Get that in your head first.

1594
01:37:29,708 --> 01:37:31,461
If I am a nobody..

1595
01:37:31,542 --> 01:37:33,826
..what drove you to come here?

1596
01:37:33,905 --> 01:37:35,573
I meant, your jeep.

1597
01:37:36,676 --> 01:37:39,342
Looks like a bit of the old Maari
is left in the auto-guy somewhere.

1598
01:37:41,493 --> 01:37:44,939
Should not be. Drop your cigarette.

1599
01:37:46,202 --> 01:37:48,284
Drop it!

1600
01:37:50,186 --> 01:37:53,510
Sir, why are you hitting him?
Careful, Maari!

1601
01:38:03,135 --> 01:38:06,047
Maari, listen. He is a cop.
Let is not cause trouble. Sir, sir.

1602
01:38:06,127 --> 01:38:08,715
Sir, we will not cause trouble.
-Trying to slither away?

1603
01:38:09,896 --> 01:38:12,855
Sir, do not hit him.
Please listen to us.

1604
01:38:12,935 --> 01:38:15,474
Do not hit him.

1605
01:38:17,846 --> 01:38:19,154
Sir..

1606
01:38:20,471 --> 01:38:27,960
No, sir. Do not hit him!
Please listen, sir.

1607
01:38:28,643 --> 01:38:31,791
Sir, please tell them to stop.

1608
01:38:31,871 --> 01:38:35,042
Stop hitting!

1609
01:38:35,122 --> 01:38:39,478
Sir, please tell them to stop.
- Okay, that is enough. Stop!

1610
01:38:42,323 --> 01:38:46,009
I am the boss here from now. Okay?

1611
01:38:46,154 --> 01:38:49,030
Either run away with your pigeons.

1612
01:38:49,110 --> 01:38:51,677
Or lie low with your
tail between your legs.

1613
01:38:51,818 --> 01:38:54,534
I wll come hit you
whenever I am bored.

1614
01:38:54,613 --> 01:38:56,913
You are my Punching Bag now.

1615
01:38:57,180 --> 01:38:58,404
Hey, give me a cigarette.

1616
01:39:09,123 --> 01:39:10,337
So..

1617
01:39:10,890 --> 01:39:14,615
When a mosquito bites a sleeping
man, it does not make it a hero.

1618
01:39:14,994 --> 01:39:18,829
One fine day, if it bites him when
he is awake, it will die in one shot.

1619
01:39:18,909 --> 01:39:20,739
One fine day..

1620
01:39:32,069 --> 01:39:33,808
Maari

1621
01:39:33,889 --> 01:39:37,288
He comes in his cop uniform,
owing we can not hit him then.

1622
01:39:37,484 --> 01:39:39,127
If only he dared
to come without it!

1623
01:39:39,431 --> 01:39:41,145
We should not keep
quiet anymore, Maari.

1624
01:39:41,354 --> 01:39:42,717
Just say the word and..

1625
01:39:42,926 --> 01:39:44,481
..we will deal with
him in other ways.

1626
01:39:47,060 --> 01:39:48,867
We need to get Velu
Anna released first.

1627
01:39:48,948 --> 01:39:50,962
How will that cop let that happen?

1628
01:39:54,649 --> 01:39:56,573
Leave! Why are you
taking me away? - Come.

1629
01:39:56,653 --> 01:39:59,132
Leave!
- Come, come.

1630
01:39:59,212 --> 01:40:02,127
Maari, I do not know anything.
I did not help him intentionally.

1631
01:40:02,261 --> 01:40:05,815
I thought he was a nice guy.
I am not on his side. - Hey..

1632
01:40:06,682 --> 01:40:08,899
I need some information
to lock him.

1633
01:40:09,426 --> 01:40:11,559
You know all about
the frauds he is committed?

1634
01:40:12,219 --> 01:40:13,539
Tell me.

1635
01:40:13,965 --> 01:40:15,728
I had lose my job if he found out.

1636
01:40:15,807 --> 01:40:19,264
If you do not tell him, you wll lose
your life. Is that okay? - Tell!

1637
01:40:19,618 --> 01:40:21,693
I do not know his
lorry routes, Maari.

1638
01:40:21,845 --> 01:40:25,773
But I do know one thing. To avoid the
checking that happens in all the tolls...

1639
01:40:25,963 --> 01:40:28,020
He uses travels vehicles
to carry small loads.

1640
01:40:28,100 --> 01:40:30,451
I know some of these routes, Maari.

1641
01:40:38,590 --> 01:40:41,444
Looks like the customs guys.
We are caught!

1642
01:40:50,601 --> 01:40:51,726
You!

1643
01:40:53,912 --> 01:40:56,039
Yes, we got it, sir.
- Means?

1644
01:40:56,119 --> 01:40:58,692
Thieves are caught!
- Open the door!

1645
01:40:58,832 --> 01:41:01,034
Bloody hell. - What?

1646
01:41:02,929 --> 01:41:04,322
Bullshit!

1647
01:41:10,599 --> 01:41:13,202
Hello? - Sir, the press and
media have come to the station.

1648
01:41:13,500 --> 01:41:15,639
Did you call them?
- What, the press?

1649
01:41:16,585 --> 01:41:18,564
We will give the entire
details of it very soon.

1650
01:41:18,716 --> 01:41:22,188
Inquiry is underway. - Sir, how
did you receive the information?

1651
01:41:30,579 --> 01:41:33,201
Officer Arjun is here! Catch him!

1652
01:41:34,376 --> 01:41:36,012
Click photo!

1653
01:41:42,435 --> 01:41:44,587
He is done so much,
but acts like he is done nothing.

1654
01:41:44,667 --> 01:41:46,377
Thank you, officer Arjun.

1655
01:41:46,457 --> 01:41:48,612
You have made our jobs easier.

1656
01:41:48,752 --> 01:41:51,601
How much you have contributed!
-He does that a lot, sir.

1657
01:41:52,337 --> 01:41:54,481
Keep up the good work.
- Thank you, sir.

1658
01:41:54,811 --> 01:41:56,608
Come here.

1659
01:41:56,689 --> 01:41:57,777
What is going on?

1660
01:41:57,856 --> 01:41:59,832
Sir, this is your doing, right?

1661
01:41:59,912 --> 01:42:02,009
You are so great!
- What?

1662
01:42:02,090 --> 01:42:05,332
When I came in the morning, the
smuggled wood and the smugglers..

1663
01:42:05,412 --> 01:42:06,467
..were outside the station.

1664
01:42:06,547 --> 01:42:11,648
I thought you caught them as usual
and called the Revenue Department.

1665
01:42:12,023 --> 01:42:15,675
Are you out of your mind?
- Not so loud, sir! - Sir, look here.

1666
01:42:17,356 --> 01:42:19,376
I did not do it.

1667
01:42:19,456 --> 01:42:22,936
Who else? How do you
get it right every time, sir?

1668
01:42:26,161 --> 01:42:28,935
You are a smart one, sir.
Right? - Maari..

1669
01:42:29,015 --> 01:42:30,669
He is so right every time..

1670
01:42:30,748 --> 01:42:33,594
..almost like he is
the one transporting it! - No!

1671
01:42:34,261 --> 01:42:36,919
He is a very nice guy!

1672
01:42:38,568 --> 01:42:42,097
Wondering why your own
goods are in your station?

1673
01:42:42,176 --> 01:42:45,289
You are not in control,
as you think, officer!

1674
01:42:45,429 --> 01:42:48,171
I stand to lose nothing with this.

1675
01:42:48,577 --> 01:42:51,052
Red sanders is transported
to Tamil Nadu from Andhra.

1676
01:42:51,934 --> 01:42:54,275
It is all happening..

1677
01:42:55,037 --> 01:42:56,985
Somebody has given..

1678
01:42:58,655 --> 01:43:02,640
It is not just the goods that were caught.
Your men were caught with it.

1679
01:43:02,720 --> 01:43:05,711
Upon enquiry, he is willing to talk.
He could talk to the Revenue Officers, too.

1680
01:43:05,792 --> 01:43:10,565
Think about what would happen to
you then. The Press is here, too.

1681
01:43:11,573 --> 01:43:15,787
This was the mosquito that bit me
when I was asleep the other day, right?

1682
01:43:16,194 --> 01:43:17,450
What did I tell you?

1683
01:43:17,529 --> 01:43:20,143
I told you, if I wake up one day and
hit you once, you will die immediately.

1684
01:43:20,224 --> 01:43:23,837
Did I say or not?
- Yes, Maari. - Right?

1685
01:43:25,225 --> 01:43:27,143
What do you want?

1686
01:43:28,215 --> 01:43:29,980
Release Velu Anna.

1687
01:43:30,176 --> 01:43:32,422
How is that possible?
We have got evidence.

1688
01:43:35,252 --> 01:43:38,293
Like you need lessons in deceit,
officer!

1689
01:43:38,373 --> 01:43:41,561
Get one of your own men to surrender
and get Velu Anna out or else..

1690
01:43:41,641 --> 01:43:42,742
Sannasi!

1691
01:43:42,823 --> 01:43:43,606
Present, sir!

1692
01:43:44,956 --> 01:43:47,833
Just checking!
How did you do it, sir?

1693
01:43:47,913 --> 01:43:52,701
It was superb. The area
has been better since you came.

1694
01:43:53,762 --> 01:43:56,635
Ask him one by one,
he wll answer patiently.

1695
01:43:56,715 --> 01:43:58,685
May I leave, officer?

1696
01:43:58,765 --> 01:44:01,414
Move, move. Careful,
do not share it on WhatsApp!

1697
01:44:01,720 --> 01:44:03,421
"That is Maari."

1698
01:44:05,009 --> 01:44:06,279
"That is Maari."

1699
01:44:08,908 --> 01:44:11,237
Maari!

1700
01:44:15,274 --> 01:44:17,094
"Maari."
- Release Velu?

1701
01:44:17,411 --> 01:44:18,966
Do not do it, man.

1702
01:44:19,149 --> 01:44:20,339
You have been an enemy all along.

1703
01:44:20,420 --> 01:44:22,347
But I was an insider
who betrayed their trust.

1704
01:44:22,427 --> 01:44:24,306
He would be very
pissed off with me.

1705
01:44:24,386 --> 01:44:28,569
Not just that, Maari's position will
get even stronger if Velu is out.

1706
01:44:28,911 --> 01:44:31,640
What can I do?
Want me to get arrested, instead?

1707
01:44:31,720 --> 01:44:34,320
Your man has been
caught red-handed.

1708
01:44:34,400 --> 01:44:38,911
This was the one thing you had to do.
And you have screwed that up, too.

1709
01:44:39,067 --> 01:44:40,247
Do not take tension unnecessarily.

1710
01:44:40,328 --> 01:44:43,168
We wll all get locked in if we are caught.
- That is why I am telling you,

1711
01:44:43,247 --> 01:44:44,902
Velu has to be released.

1712
01:44:44,981 --> 01:44:48,182
Velu has lost his political
support after he went to jail.

1713
01:44:48,262 --> 01:44:50,103
Even if he is released now..

1714
01:44:50,182 --> 01:44:53,993
He can not touch a
policeman without support.

1715
01:44:54,166 --> 01:44:55,886
You are police.. okay..

1716
01:44:55,966 --> 01:44:58,203
What if he targets us?

1717
01:44:58,456 --> 01:45:02,172
That is your problem. - Sir,
you are disassociating yourself?

1718
01:45:02,664 --> 01:45:04,711
Look, it is your
man who is been caught.

1719
01:45:04,988 --> 01:45:07,344
I can still get you
in trouble and escape.

1720
01:45:07,916 --> 01:45:10,170
Be happy that I have not done that.

1721
01:45:10,527 --> 01:45:13,619
Try to transport the
goods safely from now.

1722
01:45:16,444 --> 01:45:18,983
What is happening, Anna?
He is saying such things.

1723
01:45:19,378 --> 01:45:21,625
And there is no respect these days.

1724
01:45:22,109 --> 01:45:23,789
We need to be careful with him.

1725
01:45:33,595 --> 01:45:38,800
Move aside!
- Greetings. - Velu Anna has come!

1726
01:45:40,065 --> 01:45:42,706
Come, Maari. Put the garland.

1727
01:45:43,347 --> 01:45:45,720
Greetings, Anna.

1728
01:45:55,153 --> 01:45:59,646
Father.
- Hey.. Son..

1729
01:46:00,087 --> 01:46:02,191
I told you not to go there!
You did not listen to me.

1730
01:46:02,270 --> 01:46:06,195
Are you okay? - I am okay, dad.
- How did you get released?

1731
01:46:06,275 --> 01:46:07,925
They released Velu Annan first.

1732
01:46:08,006 --> 01:46:11,163
Then they said it was the
same case and released all of us.

1733
01:46:11,243 --> 01:46:13,240
Maari is the cause for our release.
- Okay.

1734
01:46:13,320 --> 01:46:15,614
When I heard that you had been released..

1735
01:46:15,694 --> 01:46:17,431
..I knew you had get me out somehow.

1736
01:46:17,716 --> 01:46:19,807
But why did you use this evidence?

1737
01:46:19,887 --> 01:46:22,992
It is gone waste! - You are out
of prison. What more do we need?

1738
01:46:23,753 --> 01:46:28,069
If we had gone to Revenue Department,
we could have gotten back at him.

1739
01:46:28,149 --> 01:46:29,949
Or even finished him completely.

1740
01:46:30,029 --> 01:46:32,726
Think I wll let the guy
who got you locked up get away?

1741
01:46:32,806 --> 01:46:36,011
I wll take special care of him.
You forget about it, Anna.

1742
01:46:36,091 --> 01:46:39,002
Tomorrow is the festival of lights.
And you are out of prison!

1743
01:46:39,082 --> 01:46:41,890
You just watch our
atrocity in our area today!

1744
01:46:44,381 --> 01:46:46,007
So, I am going to the barber..
- Barber..

1745
01:46:46,087 --> 01:46:47,667
You do not have any hair.
Why do you need a hair cut?

1746
01:46:47,747 --> 01:46:49,606
Go! Go!
- I am happy, Maari.

1747
01:46:49,748 --> 01:46:52,246
Because of you everyone
got released. - What?

1748
01:46:53,789 --> 01:46:56,420
What a pity!
- Who got your men out?

1749
01:46:56,500 --> 01:46:57,877
I only got Velu Annan out.

1750
01:46:57,957 --> 01:47:01,619
You were just free add ons.
Get out!

1751
01:47:01,698 --> 01:47:03,340
Hi, dude!
- Hi!

1752
01:47:04,203 --> 01:47:06,386
Look at all the reverence.
- Salute, Maari.

1753
01:47:06,514 --> 01:47:09,971
How is it going, man? - Fine, man.
- Give me a hi-5, man. - Cool!

1754
01:47:10,051 --> 01:47:11,433
You fool.

1755
01:47:16,942 --> 01:47:19,112
They are here?
It is the festival of lights indeed.

1756
01:47:19,192 --> 01:47:20,590
Start collecting in all the shops.

1757
01:47:27,047 --> 01:47:29,085
Go to the street vendor.

1758
01:47:40,829 --> 01:47:42,649
What, they are back?

1759
01:47:42,729 --> 01:47:45,333
Pay up the money.
- It is festival time.

1760
01:47:45,413 --> 01:47:47,172
So what if it is festival time?

1761
01:47:47,252 --> 01:47:48,324
Pay up!

1762
01:47:51,122 --> 01:47:52,747
Pay up, man.

1763
01:47:55,336 --> 01:47:57,936
Anna, pay up. I want to go home!

1764
01:48:05,007 --> 01:48:07,643
It is not unusual to collect,
right, Maari?

1765
01:48:10,192 --> 01:48:10,978
Poor fellow.

1766
01:48:13,810 --> 01:48:14,893
There!

1767
01:48:17,645 --> 01:48:19,686
Anna, at least you pay up, please?

1768
01:49:19,430 --> 01:49:21,904
"Maari is different now."

1769
01:49:22,643 --> 01:49:24,912
"Maari is more stronger."

1770
01:49:25,833 --> 01:49:28,086
You are wearing make up?

1771
01:49:28,167 --> 01:49:32,680
Oldie, walk away or I wll
light up this cracker on you.

1772
01:49:32,971 --> 01:49:34,501
Hey! You!

1773
01:49:34,581 --> 01:49:36,559
Come, I am going.

1774
01:49:38,158 --> 01:49:39,745
That is Maari for you!

1775
01:49:40,947 --> 01:49:41,993
Poor girl.

1776
01:49:48,734 --> 01:49:52,282
This is the usual amount.
Return this back to them.

1777
01:49:56,565 --> 01:49:58,863
Festival wishes to you!
- Same to you.

1778
01:49:58,944 --> 01:50:00,712
Bye!
- Bye!

1779
01:50:42,649 --> 01:50:48,893
"I know it looks crooked, my path.
All you straight-forward guys, get out!"

1780
01:50:48,974 --> 01:50:55,125
"It might feel a bit wrong but
it is right. This is Maari's style."

1781
01:50:55,204 --> 01:51:01,670
"This light of our lives Is Maari the
Great! Even the police salute him!"

1782
01:51:01,750 --> 01:51:08,440
"Stay if you want to.
Or walk away. Good times are here!"

1783
01:52:05,443 --> 01:52:08,541
"Bend over and people
stab you in the back."

1784
01:52:08,621 --> 01:52:11,704
"So stand tall.
That is the only life hack."

1785
01:52:11,784 --> 01:52:14,917
"When finding a partner
is like finding trouble."

1786
01:52:14,997 --> 01:52:18,111
"Being a loner
makes so much sense."

1787
01:52:18,192 --> 01:52:24,134
"Do not you say such things, son.
We are one, now and forever."

1788
01:52:24,213 --> 01:52:27,296
"Do what feels right."

1789
01:52:27,376 --> 01:52:30,798
"The doors to my home are open,
for you."

1790
01:52:30,878 --> 01:52:37,175
"I was born alone, I wll die alone.
I do not need any family."

1791
01:52:37,256 --> 01:52:43,673
"Her words oozed honey,
she came into my life."

1792
01:52:56,260 --> 01:53:02,340
"I know it looks crooked, my path.
All you straight-forward guys, get out!"

1793
01:53:02,420 --> 01:53:08,675
"It might feel a bit wrong but
it is right. This is Maari's style."

1794
01:53:08,755 --> 01:53:15,038
"This light of our lives Is Maari the
Great! Even the police salute him!"

1795
01:53:15,118 --> 01:53:22,277
"Stay if you want to.
Or walk away. Good times are here!"

1796
01:53:42,409 --> 01:53:45,086
Have the birds
returned from training?

1797
01:53:45,167 --> 01:53:47,962
We flew fifty,
only twenty have returned.

1798
01:53:49,009 --> 01:53:50,284
What about Maari's?

1799
01:53:50,538 --> 01:53:51,890
He flew thirty.

1800
01:53:52,195 --> 01:53:53,733
All thirty have returned.

1801
01:53:55,113 --> 01:53:56,467
What is funny?

1802
01:53:57,529 --> 01:53:59,205
I told you the other day.

1803
01:53:59,997 --> 01:54:02,763
That you had come to me for
help as the race draws closer.

1804
01:54:03,755 --> 01:54:05,585
What can you do for me?

1805
01:54:06,645 --> 01:54:11,140
He can not participate without his birds.
- No, do not do that. Be quiet.

1806
01:54:11,220 --> 01:54:13,934
You do not understand the seriousness
of pigeon fancying business.

1807
01:54:14,270 --> 01:54:17,957
Make sure he does not do anything.

1808
01:54:20,161 --> 01:54:22,764
Officer Arjun,
you have done so much for us.

1809
01:54:22,844 --> 01:54:26,600
Let us handle this.
- Who says I am doing this for you?

1810
01:54:28,117 --> 01:54:31,761
He should feel pain.
We need to hit him where it hurts.

1811
01:54:31,920 --> 01:54:34,210
Do not do anything without
Ravi Anna's consent.

1812
01:54:35,859 --> 01:54:37,502
It is already done.

1813
01:54:49,617 --> 01:54:50,894
Hey!

1814
01:56:16,979 --> 01:56:20,628
Maari..
Ten of our pigeons are dead.

1815
01:56:21,342 --> 01:56:23,921
They have set it on fire
when we were not around.

1816
01:56:24,136 --> 01:56:26,797
It was that girl Sridevi, who opened
the cages and saved the pigeons.

1817
01:56:27,011 --> 01:56:29,902
If it was not for her,
all the birds would be dead.

1818
01:56:30,266 --> 01:56:32,893
She burnt hands while
trying to save the birds.

1819
01:56:33,457 --> 01:56:35,900
She was here when
they burnt the cage.

1820
01:56:36,448 --> 01:56:38,780
If she had not been there,
all the birds would be dead.

1821
01:56:41,144 --> 01:56:45,103
They say pigeons never
return to a burnt cage.

1822
01:56:45,364 --> 01:56:49,134
They would have gotten scared. Our
pigeons will never return, Anna.

1823
01:56:50,908 --> 01:56:53,336
Maari, do not mistake
me for saying this.

1824
01:56:53,717 --> 01:56:55,581
Let is leave this place.

1825
01:56:55,662 --> 01:56:57,463
There is nothing here for us.

1826
01:56:57,779 --> 01:56:59,141
Why should we suffer here?

1827
01:56:59,538 --> 01:57:03,211
Velu Anna is back now.
Let him deal with the police.

1828
01:57:03,457 --> 01:57:05,273
What do we gain in these fights?

1829
01:57:05,497 --> 01:57:07,837
If pigeons were furious
then they could have attacked us.

1830
01:57:08,167 --> 01:57:11,224
What did the poor birds do to them?
I know you wll refuse to leave.

1831
01:57:12,002 --> 01:57:14,493
But, it hurts to see
you like this. Maari.

1832
01:57:14,819 --> 01:57:15,994
Let is get out of here.

1833
01:57:16,596 --> 01:57:20,167
Sannasi, pack our things
and get the vehicle ready.

1834
01:57:21,819 --> 01:57:23,255
Go!

1835
01:57:32,210 --> 01:57:34,717
Shani, see there.

1836
01:58:40,914 --> 01:58:42,886
You said pigeons do not
return to a burnt cage.

1837
01:58:44,769 --> 01:58:46,252
How did they return?

1838
01:58:47,698 --> 01:58:50,104
The birds know this is their home.

1839
01:58:50,461 --> 01:58:52,047
But you do not realise it.

1840
01:58:54,904 --> 01:58:56,713
This has to end today.

1841
01:58:58,813 --> 01:59:00,640
I told you not to do anything!

1842
01:59:00,773 --> 01:59:02,641
Everyone found out that
we set fire to his loft.

1843
01:59:02,780 --> 01:59:05,398
I have been banned from
pigeon racing altogether!

1844
01:59:05,909 --> 01:59:07,887
What about it?

1845
01:59:09,738 --> 01:59:13,037
My dignity is lost!
I can not race pigeons anymore.

1846
01:59:13,301 --> 01:59:14,490
Stop yelling!

1847
01:59:14,570 --> 01:59:17,229
Following my word got you this far.

1848
01:59:17,771 --> 01:59:19,853
So what if you can not race?

1849
01:59:20,233 --> 01:59:22,108
Playing with pigeons.

1850
01:59:22,188 --> 01:59:23,471
You will not understand that.

1851
01:59:23,699 --> 01:59:25,521
It is an ancestral sport.

1852
01:59:25,654 --> 01:59:27,337
You are following
his instructions now?

1853
01:59:27,417 --> 01:59:29,417
Anna, do not just hit me!

1854
01:59:29,597 --> 01:59:32,353
You are just a label.
Who plots the action?

1855
01:59:32,667 --> 01:59:34,621
It is our Officer Arjun.

1856
01:59:35,096 --> 01:59:38,408
So you are supporting him? Fools..

1857
01:59:38,619 --> 01:59:40,043
Do you know what you have done?

1858
01:59:40,123 --> 01:59:42,733
Do you know what Maari would do
if you lay a finger on his pigeons?

1859
01:59:42,813 --> 01:59:46,376
What is happening? - He was
just waiting for the right moment.

1860
01:59:46,456 --> 01:59:49,119
You have taunted him. He will come!

1861
01:59:57,563 --> 02:00:00,440
Fire!

1862
02:01:03,764 --> 02:01:05,224
Maari!

1863
02:01:07,212 --> 02:01:09,210
Maari!

1864
02:01:11,180 --> 02:01:13,396
Maari!

1865
02:01:14,682 --> 02:01:17,756
Maari!

1866
02:01:29,168 --> 02:01:30,427
Maari, listen to me!

1867
02:01:34,756 --> 02:01:35,981
Do not do this, Maari.

1868
02:01:43,606 --> 02:01:48,041
I only kept quiet this
long as you were a cop.

1869
02:01:48,234 --> 02:01:50,569
But you have touched my pigeons.

1870
02:01:50,854 --> 02:01:53,342
I wll kill you and
go to prison again.

1871
02:01:53,422 --> 02:01:55,282
Coward!

1872
02:01:59,445 --> 02:02:01,095
I am sorry, Maari.

1873
02:03:21,405 --> 02:03:24,077
Maari, wait! Listen to me.

1874
02:03:24,354 --> 02:03:25,596
Wait, Maari.

1875
02:03:26,742 --> 02:03:28,592
Listen to me, Maari. Listen to me.

1876
02:03:28,882 --> 02:03:31,478
I forbade that policeman,
but he threatened us to do it.

1877
02:03:31,557 --> 02:03:33,877
I had nothing to do
with your loft burning.

1878
02:03:34,059 --> 02:03:35,373
I know all about the frauds
he is committed.

1879
02:03:35,453 --> 02:03:37,514
I am willing to testify anywhere,
anytime.

1880
02:03:37,664 --> 02:03:42,247
I do not even trust a good man.
Why would I trust filth like you?

1881
02:03:45,503 --> 02:03:46,757
You were saying?

1882
02:03:47,355 --> 02:03:49,471
You wll kill me and go to prison?

1883
02:03:50,702 --> 02:03:52,752
I wll say you killed
him for revenge and..

1884
02:03:52,832 --> 02:03:54,297
..get you locked up forever.

1885
02:04:06,259 --> 02:04:09,698
You crook!
I told you not to trust him.

1886
02:04:19,039 --> 02:04:21,090
Round up everyone.
No one should escape.

1887
02:04:43,226 --> 02:04:45,259
Sir, hope you are fine.

1888
02:04:54,462 --> 02:04:57,158
What was that? You always say..

1889
02:04:57,719 --> 02:04:59,027
"I wll finish you off!"

1890
02:04:59,726 --> 02:05:02,983
See what I have done?
Now I have finished you.

1891
02:05:04,399 --> 02:05:06,835
You wll spend the rest
of your life in prison.

1892
02:05:07,680 --> 02:05:10,354
Drag him away.
- Come!

1893
02:05:10,434 --> 02:05:12,735
What are you doing?
That is not our man.

1894
02:05:12,815 --> 02:05:14,797
That is the man.
Get him. - Okay, sir.

1895
02:05:14,877 --> 02:05:16,764
Let me go. Sir.

1896
02:05:16,844 --> 02:05:18,181
Sir, why are you arresting me?

1897
02:05:18,261 --> 02:05:19,889
Let me go.
- Stop.

1898
02:05:19,969 --> 02:05:21,849
They have told us what you do.

1899
02:05:36,541 --> 02:05:38,609
I have got a guy in
the Revenue Department.

1900
02:05:39,922 --> 02:05:41,605
I wll be restored to my old power.

1901
02:05:41,949 --> 02:05:47,039
All I need is an eye-witness
to everything that Arjun has committed.

1902
02:05:47,119 --> 02:05:49,856
Sir, I am not afraid,
with Maari and you by my side.

1903
02:05:50,006 --> 02:05:51,369
I am willing to talk openly.

1904
02:05:51,449 --> 02:05:54,113
Maari!

1905
02:05:57,010 --> 02:06:00,676
What did you say? You wll finish me?

1906
02:06:03,408 --> 02:06:05,850
That was nice.
You said it real nice.

1907
02:06:06,404 --> 02:06:08,679
And do not come out, okay?

1908
02:06:08,810 --> 02:06:12,085
Just stay inside.
You wll be safer there.

1909
02:06:26,434 --> 02:06:28,056
Maari!

1910
02:06:30,420 --> 02:06:32,345
Maari!

1911
02:06:34,262 --> 02:06:36,440
Maari!

1912
02:06:58,261 --> 02:07:01,053
Sub-Inspector Arjun
has been arrested by..

1913
02:07:01,132 --> 02:07:03,894
..Revenue Department
for smuggling red sanders.

1914
02:07:27,942 --> 02:07:29,800
I can not decide whether..

1915
02:07:29,992 --> 02:07:31,637
..you are a good guy or a bad guy.

1916
02:07:32,724 --> 02:07:35,305
Why do you doubt it?
Of course I am a bad guy!

1917
02:07:35,975 --> 02:07:39,497
Good guys can not be trusted.
They can turn bad at any point.

1918
02:07:39,577 --> 02:07:43,479
Men who appear to be good
but do bad, are even worse.

1919
02:07:43,559 --> 02:07:46,288
But a guy,
who openly claims to be bad..

1920
02:07:46,368 --> 02:07:49,207
..but does some good,
can be trusted.

1921
02:07:49,949 --> 02:07:51,559
I trust you.

1922
02:07:52,873 --> 02:07:54,358
So what?

1923
02:07:54,792 --> 02:07:57,253
I feel like a lie..

1924
02:07:57,332 --> 02:07:59,121
..from a long time back...

1925
02:07:59,202 --> 02:08:02,542
..has become the truth now.

1926
02:08:02,867 --> 02:08:06,039
I am serious. I really..

1927
02:08:06,251 --> 02:08:07,579
